title: russian tea
directions: Boil spices together in 3 cups water for 3 minutes.
Strain and set aside.
Bring 1/2 gallon of water to a boil.
Add juices, lemon and spice water.
Sweeten to taste.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to boil and boil 3 minutes.
Cool. Fold in one quart of sliced strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in 10-inch skillet.
Put one thin slice of onion on each chop, also one ring of pepper on each chop.
Add 1 tablespoon of Minute rice to the center of pepper ring.
Divide the stewed tomatoes into 4 parts adding one over each chop.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake in tube pan 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Let cool in pan for minutes.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix fruit pectin and 1/4 cup of the sugar in a small bowl. Stir fruit pectin mixture into strawberries gradually.
Let stand 30 minutes; stir occasionally.
Stir remaining sugar gradually into strawberry mixture.
Stir constantly until sugar is completely dissolved and no longer grainy, about 3 minutes (a few sugar crystals may remain).
Pour into plastic containers to within 1/2-inch of tops; cover.
Let stand at room temperature 24 hours.
Jam is now ready to use.
Store in refrigerator or freeze extra containers.
Makes six 1-cup containers.

title: lemon cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water and set aside to cool. Slightly beat eggs.
Add oil and salt.
Add egg mixture and jello mixture to cake mix.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook onion until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes, or until hot and bubbling.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings. Recipe may be doubled.

title: german cheese potato soup
directions: Bring to boil the water and chicken cubes.
Add onions, carrots and celery.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add diced potatoes.	Cook 20 minutes longer.
Add chicken soup and cheese.
When melted, it's done and ready.

title: pecan drops
directions: Start oven at 325° and chop pecans rather coarsely.
Work or cream butter and shortening together until smooth, then beat in sugar gradually.
Stir in the flour thoroughly and add vanilla and pecans.
Mix well and drop by teaspoons onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until a delicate brown.

title: salmon patties
directions: In medium bowl, mix salmon, eggs, crumbs and pepper.
Mix in milk, a little at a time, until mixture will absorb no more. Shape into patties. In hot oil in skillet, heat and brown each patty on both sides.
Serve.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: spaghetti pizza(365 calories per serving)
directions: Break spaghetti into 2-inch pieces and cook according to package directions; drain and cool.
Beat egg in large bowl; add milk, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, salt and garlic salt.
Stir in cooked spaghetti and mix well.
Spread mixture evenly in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan with sides to prevent sauce from running over.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: glazed fruit
directions: Drain fruit juices into bowl.
Mix dry Jell-O with juices. Add all fruits; mix well.
Be sure to coat bananas, then chill well.

title: beef ragout with dumplings
directions: Toss beef cubes in flour seasoned with the salt, garlic salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown in the 3 tablespoons oil.
Add onion and saute lightly.
Add 2 cups of water; reduce heat to low.
Add celery, parsley, bay leaves, thyme leaves, garlic salt, onion salt and potatoes.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Stir occasionally, adding water if necessary to keep from sticking to bottom of pan.
Add carrots, green pepper and frozen peas.
Cook 1/2 hour more.
Add more water if needed.
Place dumplings on top (recipe follows), dropping with spoon.
Cook slowly uncovered for 10 minutes and covered for 10 minutes.
(Do not use self-basting cover.)
If too much liquid in pot, skim some off into saucepan. Thicken with seasoned flour to make gravy.
Serve with dumpling on top of meat and pass the gravy.
Sprinkle a little paprika over top.
Serves 4 to 6.
Expect compliments!

title: snow pudding
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water 5 minutes.
Add boiling water and sugar; stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice and chill until it begins to harden.
Beat whites of eggs to stiff froth and add to slightly hardened mixture.
Beat until spongy and chill until firm.
Serve with custard sauce.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with all other ingredients.
The easiest way to mix is to mash with fork then stir with spoon until smooth.

title: cuban black beans
directions: Rinse beans with water and leave in pressure cooker, soaking in water (twice the amount of beans) overnight or at least for 3 hours.

title: baked squash
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a baking dish.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt white chocolate or almond bark in top of double boiler. Stir in peanut butter.
When completely melted, pour onto cookie sheet.
Spread very thin.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler. When melted, spoon onto white chocolate and peanut butter mixture. Swirl on top.
Cool completely or put in freezer for 10 minutes. Take out and break into small pieces.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onions, chilies and garlic in oil until soft.
Add tomatoes, bouillon, water, tomato juice and seasonings.
Bring to boil, lower heat and let simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add tortillas and cheese.
Simmer 10 minutes more.
Enjoy with tostados.

title: whole wheat crepes
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl. Beat with rotary beater until blended. Heat a lightly greased 6-inch skillet. Remove from heat. Spoon in about 2 tablespoons batter. Lift and tilt skillet to spread batter. Return to heat. Brown on one side. Or cook on inverted crepe pan. Invert pan over paper toweling. Remove crepe. Repeat with remaining batter. Makes 16 to 18 crepes. Grease skillet occasionally.

title: my favorite chocolate chip cookie
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Blend in egg, vanilla and milk.
Mix dry ingredients
and chocolate chips together and add to egg sugar mixture. Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 15-17 minutes in a preheated 350 degree oven.

title: jello cake
directions: Beat ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Pour batter in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frosty chocolate-cherry yogurt
directions: In a blender container or food processor bowl, combine yogurt, 1 cup cherries, milk and corn syrup.
Cover and blend or process until almost smooth.
Freeze mixture in a 2 quart ice cream maker or put in a bowl and freeze in your freezer until almost firm. Add remaining cherries and chocolate pieces; continue to freeze until firm.
Yields 6 cups.

title: miner's pasties
directions: Roll out into 8-inch circles.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Using mixer, slightly cream the cheese, then add the remaining ingredients.
Chill.
If desired, roll in chopped nuts and shape into a ball before serving.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine cheeses and milk until well blended.
Pinch out bite size pieces from bread, leaving a bread crust shell to hold cheese mixture.
Pour cheese filling inside shell and arrange pieces around the plate for dipping into cheese.
When bread crumbs are gone, begin tearing pieces from the bread shell.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, brown bacon.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook until potatoes are tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 3 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: recipe for a happy life
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended into body and mind.
Store extra amounts in schools, churches, homes, neighborhoods, cities and nations.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes; cool. Pour over chicken breasts to marinate overnight or 8 hours.
Cook on grill.

title: sunday roast
directions: Place beef roast in Dutch oven or casserole dish.
Add vegetables and other ingredients.
Cover with foil.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Turn down heat to 250° and cook 2 hours.
Will not dry out or overcook while you are away.

title: gnocchi di patate al burro(potato dumplings with butter)
directions: Boil potatoes, then peel and mash with a fork or in a food processor.
Add salt, nutmeg and flour.
Blend well.

title: sundrop punch
directions: Mix juice, ginger ale and Sundrop. Chill.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Cook long grain rice according to package directions.
Saute cubed chicken in skillet or wok in approximately 1 tablespoon oil until tender.
Add vegetables, garlic and ginger to chicken and steam for 5 to 10 minutes until the vegetables are tender-crisp. Remove from heat; add rice.
Stir and sprinkle soy sauce into rice and chicken mixture until seasoned or light brown.

title: chocolate chip delight
directions: Mix.
Pour over chocolate layer.
Top with rest of Cool Whip and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Refrigerate.

title: president's dessert
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes and cool.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, 3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Then add milk, melted oleo and vanilla and pour into round, greased 9-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and 3 tablespoons cocoa as crumbs and put on top of cake batter.
Add hot water, but don't stir.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: easy potato rolls(yield:  45 rolls)
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Add potatoes, eggs and salt.
In small bowl, dissolve yeast in 2/3 cup warm water; add to cream mixture in large bowl.
Beat in 2 cups of flour and remaining water.
Add remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Shape into ball (do not knead).
Place in greased bowl; turn once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down; divide into thirds.
Shape each portion into 15 balls and arrange in 3 greased 9-inch round baking pans.
Cover and let rise until double, about 30 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on racks.

title: tahini dip
directions: Beat all ingredients to smooth paste.
Add vinegar and water as needed if paste is too thick.
Pour into serving dish. Sprinkle paprika or cayenne pepper on top if desired and garnish with fresh parsley.
Serve with pita bread.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
Spread on each ham slice and roll up.
Chill.
Cut rolls into smaller rolls.

title: broccoli cups
directions: Separate biscuits and shape into non stick muffin pan or spray cupcake pan with pam.
Mix broccoli, onion, cheddar cheese, and butter.
Fill biscuits.
Top with tomatoes.
Bake at 400° for 10-15 minutes or till nicely brown.

title: natasha's choc choc-chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Slowly, add cocoa.
Add flour and baking soda and mix well.
Stir in oats, choc-chips and nuts. Mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook stewing hen until tender, cool and bone it.
To boiling chicken broth add noodles, soups and peas.
Cook until tender, approximately 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin cracker dessert
directions: Mix and press into 13X9 pan and set aside.

title: hominy salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and serve.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until toothpick comes out dry.

title: munchible magic
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: old fashion coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add buttermilk, coconut and vanilla.
Pour in 2 Ritz pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Press the hash browns into the bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle butter over hash browns and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cook over low heat for 1 1/2 minutes after full boil.
Remove from from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter, nuts and coconut. Drop from spoon onto wax paper.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Shape into teaspoon-size balls. Place on wax paper.
Very good recipe to let your children share in making.

title: hush puppies
directions: Preheat oil in deep fat fryer to 340 degrees. Mix all ingredients together until a batter is formed. Lower basket into oil. Using a spoon drop batter by Tbsp. into oil. Cook 3-5 minutes. Makes 14 pieces.

title: candy bar pie
directions: For filling, in a medium saucepan, combine candy bars, marshmallows and milk.
Heat and stir over medium-low heat until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat; cool to room temperature.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix with mixer.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450° or at 325° for 30 minutes until set.

title: polish kielbasa pot
directions: Brown Polish sausage in oil in a large iron skillet or Dutch oven. Add sauerkraut, sugar and water to sausage.
Add potatoes and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are done. Serve with cornbread and salad.
A complete meal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and broth.
Heat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart buttered Pyrex dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery. Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients, mixing well. Bake in a casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: savory holiday stuffing
directions: Combine bread cubes, salt, pepper and sage in large bowl. Saute onion, celery and butter in skillet until tender.
Add celery and onion to bread mixture.
Add 1/2 cup water (more if needed) until mixture is very moist.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Roll into bite size balls. Bake on ungreased baking sheet, 15 to 20 minutes, in a 350° oven.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix thawed orange juice and lemonade.
Mix in water.
Add pineapple juice and chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and ice cubes.

title: coffee pudding
directions: Put coffee in boiling water; put gelatine into the milk. Bring to a boil.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except the 1/4 cup of catsup in a large bowl.
Press into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or shape into a loaf on a bake and serve platter.
Spread remaining 1/4 cup of catsup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in oleo.
Pour all ingredients into casserole dish.
Top with 2 cups grated cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease an 11 x 7-inch casserole dish.
Place cubed bread on the bottom.
Combine sugar, salt, eggs, vanilla and butter.
Add these ingredients on top of the bread.
Next, pour milk over top. If not using raisin bread, you can sprinkle with raisins and cinnamon.
Set in pan of water to bake.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: damson caramel pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar, butter and preserves.
Add the well beaten egg whites last.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer lettuce, carrots, macaroni, peas, onion and sausage.
Repeat layers.
Whip the mayonnaise, dill weed and salt together.
Frost salad with the mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup shredded Swiss cheese on top of dressing (whipped mixture).
Cover with foil and refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Cut up breasts into small pieces. Mix together soup and sour cream; pour evenly over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers over mixture.
Scatter poppy seeds over dish.
Melt butter and pour over dish.
Cook in oven at 350° until lightly browned.

title: hana chi chi
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender to a frozen consistency. Pour and drink!

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Mix together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
If using an electric mixer, beat no more than 2 minutes on low speed.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet,
about 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 to 14 minutes.
Cookies should be white when done.
Remove from cookie sheet and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sheila's calgany clam chowder
directions: Brown onion, butter and hash browns.
In separate container, combine flour and clam juice.
In a big pot, add all ingredients and heat until thick. Salt and pepper to taste. Serves many.

title: salisbury steak and onion gravy
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Shape into 6 oval steak patties and brown well on all sides.
Sprinkle flour over meat.
Mix remaining ingredients for gravy (soup, ketchup, water, Worcestershire, Tabasco and mustard).
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place the rice and corn in layers in a 2-quart casserole with tight fitting lid.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour over 1 can tomato sauce, 1/2 cup water, chopped onion and green peppers and the ground beef.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour over the second can of tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water.
Cover with strips of bacon.
Cover; bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover; bake 30 minutes longer, or until bacon is crisp.

title: sausage dip
directions: Slice cheese into 4 or 5 chunks and put in microwavable bowl or large pot (for stove).
Add evaporated milk to cheese and cook in microwave (or on stove) on low-medium heat until cheese is melted.
Stir often.
Cheese tends to harden and stick to bottom of bowl/pan.

title: cream cheese rounds
directions: Chop the green (and red if you want) peppers and onion.
Mix into the softened cream cheese.
Add hot sauce to taste and mix. Flatten the crescent rolls into 4 rectangles.
Spread the cream cheese mixture on and roll each rectangle lengthwise.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Bake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 375° (until brown).
Serve hot or cold.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add one egg at a time.
Mix in the crushed wafers then add the nuts and remaining ingredients.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Rinse and drain.
Add other ingredients and cook 20 minutes. Serve with shredded cheese, sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: dutch succotash
directions: In cooking pot melt the butter or fat and then put in the minced onions and minced green pepper, the corn and lima beans. Cook for 1 minute, then add the potatoes, diced and 1 quart of boiling water.
Cook until tender, stir in the sugar, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Serve with dumplings (Pennsylvania Dutch).

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour ingredients into an 8-inch graham cracker crust.
Freeze 15 minutes.

title: chocolate applesauce bars
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening, eggs, applesauce and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread into a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake about 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Bake until top springs back when touched.
Cut into bars while still warm.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham crumbs, sugar and oleo.
Press firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth; add 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding with milk.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip and mini chocolate chips.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix (follow box instructions) in Bundt pan. Let cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and onion. Mix 2 dressings together first, then pour on salad and mix.

title: crunch baked ham salad
directions: Combine ingredients (not the potato chips).
Stir well. Spoon this into a lightly greased 8-inch baking dish.
Top with potato chips. Bake at 400° for 20 or 25 minutes.
Will serve six.

title: thick and chunky salsa
directions: Wash tomatoes; dip into boiling water for about 30 seconds to loosen skins.
Dip into cold water.
Core and peel tomatoes; cut in half.
Squeeze tomatoes to remove most of the seeds and juice. Chop tomatoes into pieces, reserving half of them.
Put remaining tomatoes into a large saucepan.
Cook over high heat for 5 minutes.
Put cooked tomatoes through a food mill or puree with a hand blender.
Return to pot.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for about 1 hour, until mixture is reduced.
Add reserved tomatoes, onions, bell peppers, garlic, jalapeno peppers, tomato paste, salt, vinegar, sugar and cilantro.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: ann's relish
directions: Grind first 5 ingredients in blender.
Put in a plastic dishpan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup canning salt over top.
Let set overnight.
Drain and rinse in large colander.
Drain well. Bring remaining ingredients to boil.
Add peppers.
Boil 5 minutes.
Put in jars.
Process 5 minutes in hot water.

title: eric's seafood chowder
directions: Brown onions lightly in butter and add ginger. Cook vegetables in a small amount of water, adding the zucchini after squash and potatoes are partially cooked. Add clam juice and scallops. Cook a few minutes until scallops are opaque.
Add coconut milk and heat, but do not boil. Garnish with chopped fresh herbs.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine lemonade and Eagle Brand milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Blend together.
Pour into Ready-Crust (you can use graham cracker, chocolate or vanilla).

title: heavenly cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Grease bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine first 3 ingredients and 1/2 tablespoon lemon peel.
Press on the bottom and sides of pan.

title: lemon cookie bars
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Press in pan sprayed with Pam or greased.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits(just like red lobster's)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Combine Bisquick, milk and cheese with wooden spoon until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Combine butter, seasoning and garlic. Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet. Enjoy!

title: e-z shrimp dip
directions: Bring the cream cheese to room temperature and soft.
Place in the middle of serving tray in its rectangular shape.
Pour the shrimp cocktail on top of the cream cheese.
Surround with a variety of crackers for a quick, attractive and delicious appetizer!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: best ever chess pie
directions: Heat over to 425°.
Cream softened butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Beat one egg in at a time with a fork, but do not over beat.
Add meal, milk, and vinegar.
Stir until mixed in well, but do not beat hard.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and continue baking for 40-45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook beef and pork in small amount of water until tender. Pick apart into small pieces.
Add all other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate the potatoes into a bowl.
Grate the cheese in with potatoes.
Add flour.
Add egg.
Add salt and pepper.
Add oil; mix thoroughly.
Fry in margarine on medium heat in nonstick pan.
Makes 6 patties.

title: country potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes and dressing; mix lightly.
Chill 1 hour. Add celery and eggs.
Combine sour cream, onion, parsley, pickle, pimiento, mustard, salt and pepper; mix lightly.
Chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: french baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight with 1/2 teaspoon soda.
In morning, drain and cover with fresh water.
In large heavy kettle, boil until tender with 2 pounds salt pork, cut into walnut sized pieces; add salt and pepper.
Add brown sugar and ginger.
Place kettle in oven or transfer to baking dish.
Bake 4 hours at 300°.
Add water if necessary.
Be sure not to burn.
Beans will have glazy top.

title: mediterranean vegetable soup
directions: Cook the pasta. Drain. In large soup pot, combine with remaining ingredients. Simmer to blend flavors and heat through. Serve with garlic bread and a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese.

title: crepes
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender or mix by hand. Be sure you have a crepe pan. Pan and grease should be very hot. Pour about 2 tablespoons of mixture into greased pan, swirling it in a clockwise fashion quickly. Brown lightly on each side. Top with jam and roll up like a jelly roll and enjoy.

title: stuffed parmesan mushrooms
directions: Cut off the stems of the mushrooms.
Chop the stems finely. Heat the 2 tablespoons olive oil in a skillet.
Add the chopped mushroom stems, onions and garlic.
Slowly cook until lightly browned.
Combine the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, chopped parsley, salt and oregano.
Mix in the cooked onion, garlic and mushroom stems.
Stuff mixture into inverted mushroom caps and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole coated with 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until mushrooms are tender and the tops are browned.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Bring puree, juice and sugar to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes. Trim crusts from bread; cut bread into 1-inch squares.
Melt butter, then dip squares quickly into butter and place in baking dish.
Pour tomato mixture over squares.
Do not stir.
Push down lightly with fork until just coated.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cannibal "taters"
directions: In a large skillet with lid, put about 1-inch water.
Layer 1/2 of potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Place pats of margarine on top.
Repeat.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to low or simmer.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender when pierced with a fork.
Yields 6 servings.

title: biscotti a pennini(quill-shaped cookies)
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until well combined.
Add flour and mix well.
Add nuts.
Work in well and knead dough until smooth.
Roll dough into small cylinder shapes and cut on the diagonal (quill-shaped).
Place on baking sheet and bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: baked mostaccioli
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger and drain.
Add to other ingredients and simmer while cooking mostaccioli.
Drain pasta. Mix with sauce.
Add part of mixture to baking dish and cover with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining mixture and cover with a generous layer of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven until cheese is golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Place lettuce in a bowl; add cauliflower.
Spread salad dressing evenly over cauliflower.
Add onion, bacon bits and cheese.
Sprinkle sugar over top.
Cover and refrigerate.
Toss gently before serving.

title: fiesta taco dip(microwave)
directions: Spread refried beans over 12-inch pizza platter.
Set aside. Crumble meat into colander; microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring once.
Drain.
Add taco sauce and green chilies; mix well. Spread over beans.

title: asparagus and peas casserole
directions: Cook peas.
Drain asparagus, water chestnuts and mushrooms. Slice chestnuts thin.
Crumble 4 slices dry bread into 1 stick of butter.
Spread peas in pan.
Place asparagus on peas, then chestnuts and mushrooms.
Spread 1 cup mushroom soup (undiluted) over vegetables.
Sprinkle half cup grated cheese over soup.
Top with crumbs and bake until brown.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish or pan with butter.

title: hawaiian cabbage roast
directions: Cook roast with no salt in water until tender.
Remove fat and bones; drain off water and cut up in small chunks.
In large pot, boil vegetables with no salt added (about 25 to 30 minutes).
Then drain most of liquid.
Add meat to vegetable pot and pour in 3/4 bottle of soy sauce.
Cover and simmer on low for 20 to 30 minutes.
This is a surprisingly delicious meal!
Serves about 6.

title: fritz's salsa
directions: Mix.
You can eat it right away, but the flavor doesn't fully develop until refrigerated for 24 hours or more.

title: sausage nuggets
directions: Mix together all ingredients and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake mix, instant pudding and orange juice together.
Beat eggs and mix with salad oil, water, vanilla, coconut flavoring and shredded coconut.
Mix liquid and dry ingredients together.
Blend at medium speed.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mimi's delicious cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine graham crackers, powdered sugar and butter.
Press into bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan.

title: apple cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until very light, then add beaten egg. Mix and sift dry ingredients and add. Stir in apples. Drop in balls on greased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt stick of butter in 8 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Put in graham crumbs.
Cover with chocolate chips, then coconut and pecan pieces.
Pour milk over (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the ground beef, onion, egg and crushed crackers together. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pack in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Cover with desired amount of catsup.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lucy ball black beans
directions: Rinse beans and soak with one green pepper.
When beans swell, cover and cook in the same water until soft.
Add oil, minced garlic, chopped onion and 1 cup of beans, mashed, and second green pepper.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, bay leaf and sugar; boil for one more hour, covered.
Add red wine vinegar and cook slowly for the last hour.
Simmer, uncovered, until desired consistency.

title: braised sirloin tips
directions: Brown meat on all sides in a large heavy skillet.
Add consomme, juice, soy sauce, garlic powder and onion powder.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: peanut squares
directions: Combine al ingredients, except semi-sweet chocolate, and mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Melt chocolate and spread over top.
Set in refrigerator for between 15 and 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: magic fruit cake
directions: Break mincemeat into medium saucepan; add water or rum mixture; boil 1 minute.
Put in large bowl; add fruit, walnuts, dates, Eagle Brand milk and eggs.
Mix well, then add flour and soda.
Mix well.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until center sets.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in this order:
lettuce, onion, tomato and peas. Spread with Miracle Whip on top, then layer of shredded cheese. Sprinkle with Bac*Os.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook corn meal and water until a thick mush and add bacon grease.
Cook chili peppers, onions and ground meat until done. Line greased pan with mush, then meat mixture and cover with mush. Bake slowly about 2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: brandy pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce to 300° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until filling is set.

title: chewey-o's
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In oven, melt butter in jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch; rotate pan until butter covers bottom. Sprinkle cake mix over butter.
Sprinkle with marshmallows, chocolate pieces and cereal.
Pour milk evenly over top.
Bake about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
While warm, run knife around edges to loosen sides.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: holiday fruit punch
directions: Combine all the juices in a punch bowl.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale.
Stir mixture well.
Garnish with an ice ring, if desired.
Makes about 4 1/2 quarts.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour, and salt in a bowl.
Stir in unbeaten egg whites and almond extract.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased and floured baking sheets.
Bake at 325 for 20 minutes or until edges are browned.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 21 cups.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into container.
Freeze. Two hours before using, take from freezer.
When ready to serve, add 1 liter of ginger ale.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Heat oven to 350°.
Melt stick of butter in pan.
Pour butter over crunched corn flakes and set aside.
Pour mixture into buttered pan and cook for 50 minutes.
Then add corn flake mixture on top and cook 10 more minutes.
Salt and pepper in mixture to taste.

title: mamie's unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a sauce pan and boil for 1 minute stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and let cool.

title: baked scallops
directions: Melt half of butter in pan.
Cover with crumbs and garlic. Beat egg white until stiff.
Add scallops to egg white.
Spread over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour on rest of butter and parsley.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: lime-cooked shrimp with avocados
directions: In a large pot of boiling water, blanch the shrimp for 45 seconds.
Remove and drain shrimp.
Cut them in half and place them in a flat, shallow pan.
Pour 1/2 cup of lime juice over the shrimp.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and cumin.
Cover the pan and leave in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Remove shrimp and discard lime juice.
Place shrimp in a large bowl with avocados, onion, cabbage, tomato, oregano and chili flakes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate morsels over low heat.
Beat eggs and sugar in separate bowl.
Add chocolate mixture, nuts, vanilla and salt to egg mixture.
Bake in 2 pie shells at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked neck bones
directions: Place neck bones in deep/wide pan.
Cover with onion and bell pepper and sprinkle on salt, pepper and garlic.
Add 2 cups of water.
Place the top on the pan or cover with aluminum foil. Bake in oven at about 375° about 2 hours or until tender.

title: miniature pecan pies
directions: Blend cheese, butter and flour until smooth and form a ball. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or more.
Grease 24 miniature muffin tins.
Pinch enough dough to cover inside of tin to rim. Mix eggs, vanilla, brown sugar and nuts.
Fill pastry cups 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes in 375° oven or until lightly brown.
Cool on rack.
Makes 24 to 30.

title: hillbilly chicken and rice
directions: Put chicken in crock-pot, about 4 hours on high, until chicken is tender and will come off bone.
Remove meat from bone and skin. Put back in crock-pot.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook 1 cup of rice.
When rice is done, add to crock-pot.
Allow to simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Long meal.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs in large mixing bowl.
Beat well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with or without whipped cream. Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in pie shell.
Bake at 350° until pie is brown on top.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Shell and clean shrimp. Saute shrimp in butter with onion and minced garlic for 5 minutes on each side or until done. Transfer shrimp to hot serving dish and set aside. Add salt, pepper and lemon juice to butter mixture and heat for 5 minutes. Pour mixture over shrimp and sprinkle with parsley for garnish. Ready to serve over pasta or rice.

title: marti's dessert bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over melted butter.
Sprinkle walnuts, bits and coconut on top.
Drizzle the milk all over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Easy and delicious; you have to try!

title: french market soup mix
directions: Combine all beans.
Divide into 14 (2 cup) packages for gift giving and present with the following recipe for French Market Soup.
Yield:
14 (2 cup) packages.

title: scallops a la jimmy
directions: Broil 6 to 8 minutes.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash, then mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
This tastes a lot like dressing.
Very good.

title: venison stew
directions: Cook meat until tender; remove from pot.
Cut meat into small pieces.
Put meat back in pot with about 2 gallons of water.
When meat starts to boil, add onions, potatoes and carrots.
Cook until tender.
Add other ingredients and cook until desired thickness.

title: mary's salsa
directions: Clean fish and cook in 1-quart water for 30 minutes.
Remove skin and bones from fish.
Save fish and broth.
Combine rest of ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.
Add fish and broth from fish. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cajun pasta
directions: Cook and drain pasta. No matter what your mother told you, don't rinse the pasta unless you like all the sauce on the bottom of your bowl. Cook pasta sauce with shrimp, carrots and mushrooms to light simmer. Add as much Cajun seasoning as your taste buds can handle. Toss pasta with sauce well. Serve warm.

title: pink fruit freeze
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, ice cream and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Freeze until firm.
Place in refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
Garnish with cherries, mint and holly leaves.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: buttery oatmeal crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Line a cookie sheet with foil; set aside. In a large bowl combine oats, sugar, flour, and baking powder; set aside.
In another bowl combine melted butter, corn syrup and cream.
Add butter mixture to oat mixture and stir until combined. For each cookie, drop dough by rounded teaspoons 3 inches apart onto the prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 min. or until bubbly and golden brown around the edges.
Cool the cookies on foil. Carefully lift edges of cookies and then peel cookies off foil.
In a small heavy saucepan heat chocolate pieces and shortening over low heat until melted, stirring occasionally.
Dip one half of each cookie into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to cool until chocolate is set.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: bowknots
directions: You will also need 24 toothpicks.
Trim crusts.
Spread soup on one side of bread slices.
Roll each slice from one corner to other.
Wrap bacon strip around middle and secure with toothpick. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Dry, crisp and delicious.

title: mexican meatball soup
directions: In a bowl, mix ground round, egg, 1/2 of onion, herbs, salt and pepper.
Roll in balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Heat stock to simmer; drop meat balls in hot stock.
Add remaining onion. Simmer approximately 20 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook until vegetables are done.
Bouillon cubes may be used for beef stock. Very good on a cold day.

title: shrimp mold
directions: In saucepan, cream together over low heat the cream cheese, mayonnaise, tomato soup and gelatin.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into mold.
Chill.
Serve on crackers or small bread.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Use frying chicken (skinned or not), cut in pieces.
Combine margarine and oil in shallow baking pan.
In flat dish, mix oregano, garlic powder, paprika and bread crumbs.
Dip chicken in oil mixture and roll each piece in bread crumb mixture.
Place in baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the chicken.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch dish or pie plate 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Cook and stir bacon and onion over medium heat until bacon is browned and onion clear; drain well.
Spread in plate. Beat milk, baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Cook thighs in lightly salted water until done.
Cool.
Cut meat from bones.
Save broth.
Saute celery and onions in butter. Mix all ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Add broth if needed to moisten.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Periodically add broth if it becomes too dry.
Casserole is ready when wild rice is fully open.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In frypan, brown ground beef with onion.
Drain excess fat.
Add tomato soup, sauce, carrots, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top and add separated refrigerated biscuits.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are no longer doughy.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: meatza pie
directions: Mix meat, milk, bread crumbs and garlic salt.
Lightly pat into the bottom of a jelly roll pan.
Spread ketchup over the meat. Arrange mushrooms on top.
Cover with shredded cheese. Sprinkle oregano and Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake in hot 450° oven for 20 minutes.

title: olive salad
directions: Mix well.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Cover and let stand 1 hour or refrigerate and take out 1 hour before serving.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.
Mix in other ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Mix 20 soda crackers, crushed, and 1 stick oleo, melted.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chop marinade
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate pork chops for 3 to 4 hours. (Makes enough for 8 pork chops.)

title: war cake, eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Boil this 3 or 4 minutes.
Cool.
Add flour to thicken (when cool).
Add 1 teaspoon soda, 1 teaspoon baking powder, nuts and cocoa.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: new england pot roast
directions: Cook beef in Dutch oven over medium heat until brown.
Reduce heat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread horseradish over both sides of beef.
Add 1 cup water.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer on top of range or cook in 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook until tender, about 1 hour.
Remove to platter.
Skim excess fat from broth.
Add enough water to broth to measure 2 cups.
Shake 1/2 cup cold water and the flour in tightly covered container.
Stir gradually into broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Serve gravy with beef.
Makes 8 servings, 370 calories per serving.

title: a-1 roast
directions: Mix steak sauce, mushrooms with juice and garlic powder in a small bowl. Place roast in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Top with steak sauce mixture. Cover tight. Bake at 350 degrees for 2 hours. Remove roast from pan and slice. Pour mushroom mixture in a saucepan. Blend cornstarch with 1/4 c. cold water and add to mushroom mixture. Cook until it starts to thicken. Pour over roast.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, marshmallows and bananas.
Stir in sugar. Mix well.
Sprinkle on gelatin and stir.
Fold in whipped topping. Refrigerate.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and add one container of Cool Whip; mix well.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: pecan chicken
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 pieces of waxed paper. Flatten to 1/4-inch using mallet or rolling pin.
Set aside. Combine honey and mustard.
Spread on both sides of chicken and dredge in chopped pecans.
Bake in lightly greased shallow baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: harvest cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Combine sugar and apples; let set 1 hour. Beat eggs, vanilla and oil until frothy.
Mix in 1/4 of dry ingredients.
Blend in apples, walnuts, raisins and remaining dry ingredients.
Place in greased and floured cake pan or 9 x 12-inch glass dish.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream vanilla, Crisco, oleo and sugar.
Add beaten egg. Dissolve soda in hot water and mix alternately with flour and salt.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(All white flour can be used.)

title: chocolate clair cake
directions: Mix pudding and sugar in bowl. Add milk and mix until smooth and thickening. Fold in Cool Whip. Mix. Use a 9 x 13 pan or dish. Put in layer of whole graham crackers, layer of pudding mix, layer whole graham crackers, layer of pudding mix, layer of whole graham crackers, layer of pudding mix, layer of graham crackers on top. Spread frosting on top of crackers. May sprinkle with nuts. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all fish together; put in casserole (9 x 13-inch).
Mix soup with milk and pour over fish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Beat together the shortening, sugars and eggs.
Sift the flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add oats.
Add dry ingredients and boiling water to first mixture and mix.
(This batter will be very thin, but it thickens as it bakes.)
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes in a greased 8-inch pan.

title: eggs goldenrod
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, melt butter and stir in flour. Gradually add the milk, stirring constantly to prevent lumps. Continue cooking until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted and mixed well.
(More cheese can be added to taste.)
Add chopped eggs and stir just until they are coated with cheese sauce.
Pour over toasted muffin halves.
Good for Sunday brunch.

title: baked chicken stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken in flour mixture.
Brown chicken slowly in butter in skillet; transfer to baking dish.
Add onion and garlic to skillet drippings; stir in lemon juice, chicken broth and mushrooms.
Simmer for about 5 minutes; pour over chicken.
Cover baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hobo supper
directions: Make hamburger patties; salt and pepper to taste.
Place on aluminum foil; cover with potatoes, carrots and onions.
Fold wrap.
Place in another piece of foil; wrap.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Cherries may be added for garnish.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash
berries
and
stem.
Turn
1 pint of best berries upside down on bottom of pie shell (baked).
Put other pint of berries in	blender.
Add 1 cup sugar and 4 tablespoons cornstarch; blend until liquid.
Add red food coloring until it is bright red.
Put in	a pan over low heat and stir until boiling.
After it boils in a rolling boil, boil 1 minute and take off	heat.
Pour over strawberries in pie shell and let it set in
refrigerator until chilled well.
Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: cherry chocolate pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heavily spray Bundt pan with nonstick spray, or oil and dust with flour.
Evenly distribute 1/4 cup of the pecans in bottom of pan.

title: chocolate pudding and cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa in mixing bowl.
Combine vanilla, milk and melted margarine.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Turn into 8-inch square pan.

title: date pudding
directions: Put dates in bowl and pour boiling water over dates.
Let set to cool, then add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350°.
When cold, cut in bite-size pieces.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Combine crumbs and margarine. Press firmly into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Mix cornstarch with a little water and stir all ingredients well.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Do not disturb.

title: gold rush brownies
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch oblong baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°.
Let cool for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut and remove from pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together well and chill.
Add 1 can shoestring potatoes just before serving.

title: blueberry cupcakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Roll blueberries in flour and gently fold into batter.
Fill muffin cups that have been lined or greased and sprinkle sugar on top before baking. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: iced tea
directions: Boil water.
Drop in all tea bags for 30 minutes.
Stir in sugar and cold lemonade.

title: onions au gratin
directions: Chop
onions,
not small, more like chunks.
Mix onions with 1 1/2 cup cheese and remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2 quart casserole baking dish.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add the two mixtures together.
Add one can of drained fruit cocktail and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into long baking pan.
DO NOT grease or flour pan.
Add 1/2 cup coconut sprinkled on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mama's greek cheese appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix Bisquick, buttermilk and eggs.
Spread in pan.
Drizzle with melted margarine and sprinkle with cheese and salt.
Bake until a deep, golden brown, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares, then cut squares diagonally into halves.
Garnish with chopped or sliced olives of choice. Makes 4 dozen appetizers.

title: sweet and sour meatball bake
directions: Combine egg, wheat germ, soy sauce, garlic powder and pepper. Add pork and mix well.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
Spray large skillet with Pam.
Add meatballs and cook over medium heat until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers, leaving 6 thin evenly spaced lengthwise strips of rind.
Slice cucumbers into 1/16-inch thick rounds.
Set in colander.
Toss with salt.
Cover with towel and weight with heavy bowl for 1 hour to remove excess water.
Pat cucumbers dry. Dissolve sugar in vinegar in large bowl.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Season with pepper and toss well.
Refrigerate.
Can be served the same day or for a more assertive flavor, it can be marinated for up to 2 weeks.
Serve well chilled.

title: green chili
directions: Cover all ingredients with water and cook slowly.
Thicken with flour.
Serves 6.

title: easy herbed grilled salmon
directions: Preheat grill. Make a tray out of heavy-duty foil by folding a long piece in half and folding up all 4 sides with the dull side up. Spray the bottom of the foil tray with cooking spray. Place fish filet in the tray, skin side down. Smear a thin line of butter on filet. Squeeze lemon juice liberally over filet and then a splash of white wine. Sprinkle remaining seasonings lightly over filet and transfer the foil tray to the hot grill. Cover. Cook for 10 minutes per inch of thickness of filet. DO NOT overcook or it will be dry and unpalatable. Turning is not necessary. Salmon is done when it turns a light pink color throughout.

title: vegetable platter
directions: Select a 12-inch glass platter.
Arrange broccoli pieces around outside edge, then cauliflower, carrots and pepper in concentric circles.
Dot with butter slices.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute peppers and onions in butter.
Add squash, tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and water and stir into squash mixture.
Cook until thickened, turn into casserole and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: alabama break away breakfast bread
directions: In a Bundt pan, arrange 1 can of the biscuit quarters dipped in melted margarine. Top with onions, peppers, bacon bits and cheese. Arrange another can of the dipped,

quartered biscuits over the first layer. Add another layer of onions, peppers, bacon and cheese. Arrange the 3rd can of quartered biscuits on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown on top. Serve hot! Enjoy!

title: taco salad
directions: Toss with 1/4 cup Catalina dressing.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
While still hot, dissolve cranberry sauce in Jell-O and water mixture.
Let cool slightly and add the remaining ingredients.
Set in bowl or mold.

title: seafood soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic.
Remove from saucepan.
Add margarine and flour to make a pale roux.
Slowly whisk in milk.
Add onion mixture, crab meat and remaining seasonings.
Cook over low heat 15 to 20 minutes to blend flavors.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. Reheats well.
Can be frozen.
Can be made with skim milk.
Great with a green salad for a light dinner.

title: austrian tomato salad
directions: Step 1:
In medium bowl, stir together tomatoes, green pepper, onion and parsley.
Set aside.

title: soda cracker bar
directions: Place soda crackers on cookie sheet lined with foil and sprayed with Pam.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
Drain and cool.
Cut onions and green peppers in round slices or however you prefer and mix with cooled carrots. Mix other ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate for 12 hours or more.
This will keep for 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make white sauce of the oleo, flour, milk, salt and pepper. Put layer of potatoes in a 1-quart dish.
Add a layer of onion. Repeat, then add white sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Mix jello and sugar together.
Add boiling water until jello-sugar is dissolved; cool.
Add pineapple juice and freeze. Thaw at least 2 hours at room temperature.
Add 7-Up or ginger ale when ready to serve.
Should have ice crystals (no ice cubes necessary).

title: lazy day overnight lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown meat.
Drain well.
Add sauce and water and blend well.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, chives, oregano and egg; mix well.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Save 1 cup of dry cake mix.
Put aside.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat 1/2 the oil and simmer the tomatoes for 10 minutes.
In another frypan, heat the remaining oil and saute the onions and garlic for 5 minutes.
Add the pepper, zucchini and eggplant to the onions.
Cook over a low heat for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add the tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste and a pinch of sugar.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: chicken party pie
directions: Combine sour cream and mayo.
Add 2/3 cup of this mixture to chicken, pineapple, nuts and celery.
Mix well.
Fill baked cheese pastry shell.
Top with remaining sour cream and mayo mix. Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Sift flour and baking powder.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately. Add vanilla. Fold in well beaten egg whites, but do not beat.
Makes 5 thin layers or 4 medium size layers.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done, drain.
Prepare 9-inch pie crust. Mix cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle in shell.
Lightly beat eggs in a bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture. Pour in shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, soup, veggies, water and butter into casserole dish. Place biscuits on top and bake at 350 degrees till golden brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well.
Gradually mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In large casserole bowl, mix all ingredients except margarine. Place margarine in spoonfuls on top.
Bake at 400° for about one hour, until thick and lightly brown.
Sprinkle with additional cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is completely melted.

title: hawaiian cream cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 15 x 10 1/2 x 2-inch greased and floured pan for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and condensed milk.
Do not boil.
When chips are melted, remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup miniature marshmallows and nuts.
Pour in buttered dish.
Cool and cut.

title: creamy pepper dip
directions: In a medium bowl, stir cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time, at least 2 hours.
Garnish with pepper rings.
Serve with fresh vegetables or crackers for dipping.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups. Double, if needed.

title: upside-down pineapple cake
directions: Melt butter over low heat in skillet.
Sprinkle sugar and arrange pineapple on sugar.
Let stand.
Mix other ingredients at high speed for 4 minutes.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 45 or 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Do not cover until completely cool.

title: candy pudding
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil. Add cream slowly; keeping mixture boiling. Cook to a firm ball stage when dropped into cold water. Pour on marble slab and when cool work with heavy spoons or forks. Divide candy into three parts when creamed. Put melted chocolate in one part, cherries and a few drops of red food coloring in one and nuts in the third part. It is best to make chocolate part a little bigger than the other two since the added cherries and nuts increase the volume of the other two. Shape into three long rolls. Put the chocolate roll on the bottom, the cherry roll in the middle and the nut roll on top. Ice with melted, but not too hot semi-sweet chocolate. Use a pastry brush.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients as for any bread dough.
Fold in apricots and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf tins about 55 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar, flour and beaten eggs.
Add pineapple, undrained. Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Toss bread cubes in melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together.
Add pecans (optional), coconut (optional) and marshmallows; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill before serving.

title: ambrosia
directions: Peel and cut up oranges.
Add pineapple with juice. Add coconut and marshmallows. Mix with sour cream and sugar.
Will keep and be good several days.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken soup with lukshin
directions: Wash and clean chickens. Put in large pot and fill with cold water to top. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of salt.

title: mutton leg-romania(pulpa de berbec la tava)
directions: Wash mutton and remove excess fat.
Debone the meat.
Rub with salt and let sit for 30 minutes.
Interlace bacon and garlic pieces.
Roll meat and tie with a string.
Place in roasting pan greased with lard, add 2-3 Tbsp. of water, add 1 more Tbsp. of lard.
Add wine or vinegar and place in oven in high heat until it starts to brown, then reduce heat to medium.
Baste meat occasionally with liquid in the pan.
Add 2-3 Tbsp. of water as needed.
Cook until meat is done and tender.
Serves well with mashed potatoes and carrots.
This roast is excellent served cold.

title: molly hogan
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients in a blender until fluffy.
Transfer to a large pitcher and add a fifth of gin to make a "batter".
Pour one double shot of "batter" over ice in a 9 ounce glass.
Fill glass with 7-Up; add an orange slice and enjoy.
Makes about 25 servings; great for parties.
Orange Julius with a kick.

title: o'hara's green rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in casserole dish 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off fat and add rest of ingredients except cheese.
Heat flour tortillas in skillet; lay tortillas in 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Roll meat and some cheese up in tortillas and layer in pan until pan is full.
Pour leftover meat sauce over top of filled tortillas.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes; last few minutes sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake until melted.

title: shrimp rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Rinse shrimp under cold water; drain thoroughly.
Combine in square casserole dish:
rice, shrimp and Cheddar cheese soup.
Mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over entire top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until casserole is blended and bubbly.
Serve from casserole dish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes; prepare and chop all other vegetables and combine with tomatoes.
Boil gently for 2 hours, stirring frequently.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Cook over simmer flame 1 hour longer, stirring occasionally.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: cranberry orange salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed.
Grind oranges (rind and all).
Add cranberries, pecans and sugar.
Mix with jello that has begun to jell.
Slice and serve on lettuce, if desired, with a dab of mayonnaise.

title: simple pasta
directions: Bring chicken broth (add water if needed to cover pasta) to a boil.
Add pasta (follow directions on package).
Chop parsley, garlic and basil and grate cheese. Drain pasta and put on individual plates.
Each can add the other ingredients to taste.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Or use 1 1/2 cups plain flour, 1 1/2 cups self-rising flour and omit baking powder.

title: garden harvest
directions: Cut corn from cobs.
Place corn in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add onion and green pepper.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave High 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except tomato.
Cover and microwave at High, 7 to 8 minutes, stirring once.
Add tomato.
Cover and microwave at High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 4 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream the shortening and sugar together. Beat eggs and add in.
Blend bananas into mixture.
Mix flour and baking powder together. Add into mixture.
Stir in nuts. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan or 2 pound coffee can for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool, slice and enjoy.

title: mary ann's fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar in bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: tossed salad dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients together in a jar; cap and chill in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: cheese cake frosting
directions: Cream the cheese and oleo. Add powdered sugar, vanilla and coconut. Spread over cake; top or sprinkle cake with pecans.

title: sheet cake
directions: Melt butter, cocoa and hot water.
Mix well with flour and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 19 minutes.

title: sandies
directions: Beat butter for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add vanilla and 2 teaspoons of water; beat well.
Stir in flour and pecans.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven about 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Gently shake on powdered sugar.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: whacky cake
directions: In a bowl, sift the dry ingredients.
Make 3 holes in this mixture. Add the oil, vinegar and the vanilla, filling the holes. Pour the cold water over the top. Stir with a fork.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool and frost. Easy and delicious!

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Salt lightly. Top with chips, then cheese.
Combine soup and milk and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered; then another 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes in a long pan.

title: baked rice
directions: Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add ice cream.
Stir until melted completely.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill in refrigerator.
Congeals rapidly.
Cut in squares.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed; omit butter. Substitute 1 cup beer for 1 cup water in each package of rice. Add rest of water as called for. Add curry powder to mayonnaise and into rice.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: fruit pops
directions: Dissolve the first 3 ingredients in 2 cups boiling water.
Add the cold water.
Freeze until firm.
Makes 18 pops.

title: salad dressing for eggs
directions: Put all ingredients except vinegar in a small saucepan; mix well and bring to a boil.
Add vinegar, stirring constantly.
Put in piece of butter the size of a walnut.
Boil until thick.
To serve, cut boiled eggs in half and pour sauce over them.

title: apricot coffee cake
directions: Mix all in bowl.
Pour 1/2 of batter into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread can of apricot pie filling over batter.
Top with rest of batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Add whipped cream. Blend in pecans and cherries.

title: chocolate mint squares
directions: Crush wafers; sprinkle 2/3 of crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream butter and powdered sugar together; add the beaten egg yolks, melted chocolate and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Spoon on top of crumbs; cover with remaining crumbs.
Freeze until solid.
Cover with chocolate chip mint ice cream.
Freeze.
Keeps well in freezer.

title: special cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 350°
oven until slightly brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: homemade chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken (boil and debone); set aside.
Take 1 cup broth from chicken.
Mix with the flour and salt.
Place on floured surface.
Roll out with rolling pin.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch slices with knife.
Pick up and pinch to desired length.
Drop into boiling broth.
Cook until tender.
Add 1 can of cream of chicken and stir.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: In large saucepan, combine cheese, Parmesan, butter and milk. Stir constantly until smooth.
Toss pasta lightly with sauce, coating the pasta well.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: potato chowder
directions: In heavy kettle, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to drain. To drippings, add carrot, potato, salt, onion and boiling water. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Add sage, paprika, pepper and parsley.
Measure flour into bowl and gradually blend in milk.
Stir into vegetable mixture; cook until soup thickens. Crumble bacon over each serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into popsicle molds. Place in freezer.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in water for 10 minutes, drain and cool.
Mix the onions and pepper with carrots.
Mix all other ingredients; add to carrots as a marinade.
Store in refrigerator at least 12 hours before serving.
Keeps a long time.

title: orange cake
directions: Bake according to directions on box. As soon as cake is removed from the oven, pour or spoon some of the Orange Glaze mixture between cake and side of pan.
Remove cake from cake pan. Make slits with knife in cake.
Pour remaining glaze over cake.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and 1 tablespoon grated orange peel. Stir dry ingredients together.
Alternately stir in the flour mixture with 1/2 cup orange juice until blended.
Pour into a
greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for 15 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool for 45 minutes.

title: hot pepper pie
directions: Line an 8 or 9-inch pie pan with green chilies or jalapeno peppers, sliced or dried.
Grate cheese and fill pan.
Beat eggs and pour over cheese.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold into batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 22 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely.

title: apricot bars
directions: Melt butter and sugar; cool.
Add oatmeal.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and add to butter mixture.
Add nuts.
Reserve 1 cup mixture.
Put remainder of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes. Start counting when mixture has reached a full boil.
Remove from fire and add oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter, if desired. Beat until well blended.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: salsa
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in food processor.
Add chopped tomatoes.

title: french dressing
directions: Boil vinegar and sugar for 3 minutes and cool.
Add oil, catsup, onion, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into clean container and add whole garlic cloves, if using.
Refrigerate and let blend before using.
Recipe can be halved.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake flour, baking soda, sugar and salt together.
Add sour cream and shortening; beat for 2 minutes.
Add melted chocolate, vanilla, eggs and hot water.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 25 minutes for sheet cake and 25 minutes for layer cake or until springs back when touched.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan and put in half of the bread cubes.
Place the processed cheese and ham over the bread.
Add the remaining bread.
Beat the eggs, milk and seasonings together. Add onion flakes.
Pour mixture over bread, ham and cheese. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until set. Cut into wedges.

title: buckeye peanut butter rolls
directions: Mix well with hands and form into balls.
Let set.
Melt a 12 ounce package chocolate chips with 1/3 cake of wax in a double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and put on waxed paper.
Makes about 80 balls, depending on size you make.

title: sticky buns
directions: Make sauce of first 3 ingredients.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When thickened, pour into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Set aside.

title: pizza bites
directions: Mix margarine and garlic.
Spread on muffin
halves. Cut each muffin half into 4 wedges.
Place 1 slice pepperoni and 1 tomato half on each muffin wedge.
Place in broiler pan.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook meats.
Chill overnight and skim fat off.
Add all ingredients and simmer until done.
Simmer for several hours.
If stew is too thin, add a few crushed saltine crackers.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake about 30 minutes at 300°.
Remove from oven and put on topping.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Combine all and heat.

title: pistachio fluff
directions: Mix butter and crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes. Let cool completely.
Mix milk with pudding mix. Add ice cream. Spread over crust. Spread on Cool Whip and refrigerate overnight.

title: party chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips, in a large bowl.
Beat slowly at first, then at high speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in chips. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: bisque of crabmeat and mushrooms
directions: Thaw crabmeat.
In medium skillet, melt 4 tablespoons butter. Saute onion, green pepper, scallion, parsley and mushrooms until soft, but not brown.
Reserve.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve both Jell-Os in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice. Set aside to thicken slightly.
Whip Pet milk.
Combine cream cheese and marshmallow cream.
Add whipped milk.
Fold ingredients in Jell-O mix.
Add crushed pineapple.
Put in serving bowl and chill.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Slice carrots diagonally.
Combine all ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes, until tender.
Ready to serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in dry ingredients, then fold in apples, nuts and vanilla (mixture will be very thick).
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.

title: spinach salad and dressing
directions: Wash and place spinach in
large salad bowl.
Drain and add mandarin oranges along with broken walnuts.

title: mama's cinnamon-raisin cookies
directions: Cream together brown and white sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, cinnamon, vanilla and raisins.
Slowly add flour.
Add baking soda that has been dissolved in 2 teaspoon milk.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: chicken stir-fry on rice
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil in a covered medium size saucepan. Stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand while preparing chicken.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add 1 box of Jiffy corn muffin mix. Bake in a greased hot pan or skillet at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: low cholesterol pie crust
directions: Mix together; pat in pie pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Fill with favorite filling.

title: turtle bar cookies
directions: Melt caramels with cream or milk in double boiler.
Mix flour, oatmeal, salt, soda, brown sugar and melted butter.
Pat 1/2 of this mixture in a 9 x 12-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter delight cookies
directions: Mix sugar and milk and melt; add cocoa.
Boil for 5 minutes. Turn off heat.
Add vanilla, butter, peanut butter and oats.
Drop on plastic wrap and cool in refrigerator.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli with 1 teaspoon salt.
Drain and saute onions in margarine.
Add cheese and seasoning.
Cook on medium heat.
Add other ingredients.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Make mix according to package.
Add 3 tablespoons creme de menthe.
Place in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake until top springs back.
While warm, spread 1 can
hot fudge sauce over top.
Cool completely.
Mix 3 tablespoons creme de menthe in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled cake.

title: homemade cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together, then add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° until done; let cool.

title: strawberry cream
directions: Have strawberries partially thawed.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add partially thawed strawberries, pineapple and mashed banana.
Divide mixture in half.
Pour half in dessert bowl and set in refrigerator.
After jello has set, spread sour cream over jello mixture.
Add remaining jello and set in refrigerator again.
Serve with Cool Whip on top if desired.
Makes enough for 6.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix chocolate chips, cinnamon, sugar and nuts together.
Mix other ingredients for batter.
Pour 1/3 of batter in pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Put 1/2 package of chocolate chip-brown sugar mixture and batter. Pour remaining batter, then sprinkle with rest of mixture and top with chocolate chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well. Chill overnight. Serves 12.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix wet ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients.
Blend both parts together.
Add prunes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, melt butter; add onion and cook until transparent.
Place in casserole dish with rice and beef consomme.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave home run burgers
directions: In 1 1/2-quart bowl or casserole, combine ground beef and onion.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 5 minutes, stirring 3 times. Drain off fat.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 4 minutes, stirring after every 2 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve on buns.
Makes 8 to 9 servings.

title: maple pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Beat in next 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.

title: easy pickles
directions: Layer pickling cucumbers and onions in deep container.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly until sugar is dissolved.
Pour on cucumbers and onions.
Cover and refrigerate.
Pickles are ready to eat after 24 hours.
Pickles can be stored in refrigerator up to 1 month.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cinnamon - sugar muffins
directions: Mix Crisco
and
1/2 cup sugar together and cream thoroughly. Add egg and beat well.
Sift plain flour, measure and sift again with
baking
powder,
salt
and nutmeg.
Stir dry ingredients into
creamed
mixture
alternately
with milk and blend thoroughly.
Bake
at
350° in greased muffin tins.
Mix together 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Melt margarine and dip the baked muffins in before rolling in sugar and cinnamon mixture. Serve warm or cold.
Makes 12.

title: mississippi red sauce for ribs
directions: Simmer ribs in pot of salted water about an hour to an hour and a half, just until tender; let cool.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
In a small bowl, mix the rest of the
ingredients. Spread over the ribs, saving the rest for basting.
Cook over medium-hot fire or in broiler.
Grill, turning and basting, until brown and crusty, about 15 minutes.

title: peaches - fresh to frozen
directions: Add peaches to sugar and juice; let stand 1 hour. Pack in containers and freeze.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Heat milk. Combine sugar, cornstarch, coca, and salt. Add warm milk and stir thoroughly with wire wisk. Cook until mixture thickens. Add vanilla and margarine. Serve immediately over buttered home made biscuits.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Place croutons on bottom.
Top with sausage.
Combine eggs, milk and dry mustard. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
