The next morning, preheat oven to 300°.
Spread onions on top and cover with mushroom soup. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for approximately 1 hour.

title: homemade pizza
directions: For crust, mix hot roll mix according to crust recipe on box. Roll out, place on pizza pan and allow to bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cover with pizza sauce, add cheese, then top with your favorite topping.
Sprinkle with pizza seasoning.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and crust is brown.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Squeeze
juice of lemon and add to rest of ingredients, folding in egg whites last.
Bake in unbaked shell at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until center tests clean.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in greased loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken my way
directions: Simmer chicken with all the vegetables and herbs until tender. Remove the chicken from the stock after cool. Skin the chicken and cut into 4 pieces.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter in large shallow pan over low heat.
Stir in worcestershire and seasoned salt.
Add cereals and nuts.
Mix over low heat until all pieces are coated.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes.
Spread out on absorbent paper to cook.
Yields 7 1/5 cups.

title: coconut pie(no crust)
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well and pour into 2 (9-inch) pie plates.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook noodles according to package directions. Add soup, milk and tuna. Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peach pickles
directions: Bring ginger, vinegar, sugar, cinnamon sticks and salt to a boil.
Put peaches in until tender.
Put peaches in jar and pour mixture over and seal.

title: refrigerator potatoes
directions: Grease lightly a 4 quart casserole dish.
Peel and cook potatoes.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Mash potatoes.
Add sour cream and cream cheese mixture.
Add other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover tightly.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes with lid on first half, then remove.
Garnish with shredded cheese and serve.
The potatoes will fluff up again after they have been baked.
Can stay in refrigerator for a week.

title: chiffon cream pie
directions: Beat egg white in a fairly large bowl until foamy.
Add the sugar, a little at a time, while beating to form a meringue.
Set aside.
Mix egg yolk into pie mix very carefully until no lumps can be seen.
Stirring constantly, add milk and cook on medium-high heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Fold into meringue and let cool.
Pour onto a baked and cooled pie shell. Mixture thickens as it cools.

title: peach salad
directions: Pour gelatin in pan.
Pour pineapple over this and heat to dissolve.
Cool in refrigerator until begins to congeal.
Add buttermilk and stir.
Congeal a little more, then add nuts and whipped topping.
Stir well and congeal firm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine thoroughly the sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add slowly to dry mixture the milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into cooled, baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and cook in 350° oven until peaks are brown.

title: oyster pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Saute onion and celery.
Set aside.
In saucepan, melt butter, add flour and salt.
Mix.
Add evaporated milk and enough oyster juice to make 1 1/2 cups of white sauce.
Place oysters, potatoes, celery and onion in bottom crust.
Pour white sauce in.
Cover with top crust.
Aerate by using a knife to slit a few small holes in top crust.
Be sure top crust and bottom crust are well sealed.
Place on aluminum foil on cookie sheet.
Cook for 30 minutes or until crust is done.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Cream
butter;	add
beaten eggs and mashed beans; sift dry ingredients
together.
Add
sugar	mixture, then apples, nuts, raisins
and vanilla.
Mix well; pour into well greased and floured
tube
or
Bundt
pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes. Glaze and decorate with nuts and cherries.

title: creamy chicken shortcake
directions: Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions.
While it's baking, fry bacon in medium size saucepan until lightly browned.
Add butter; heat until melted.
Stir in flour until blended.
Gradually stir in broth, then milk.
Stir over medium heat until mixture simmers.
Simmer, stirring often, for 4 minutes, until thickened.
Add green onion, pimento, hot pepper sauce and chicken; cook and stir for about 2 minutes.
Cut cornbread into 8 squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Prepare broccoli in water as directed on package.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients together.
Mix well. Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May add bread crumbs if desired.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil corn syrup, brown sugar, butter and salt for 5 minutes. Take off stove; add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Spread into 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 225°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip
cheese and sugar until creamy.
Add peanut butter and blend.
Add milk and blend.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture. Pour into
pie
shell; freeze.
Cover after frozen and it will keep
a long time.	Before serving, remove from freezer about 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Mix broth and soup in large pan and bring to a boil. Add steamed broccoli and reduce heat. Simmer, covered for about 5 minutes.
Heat butter in pan and add chopped onion, saute until tender.
Add flour to butter & onions.
Cook for 1-2 minutes. Gradually stir in milk with onion and flour mixture.
Cook until thickened, about 5-10 minutes. Add salt and pepper, mix well. Stir milk mixture into broccoli mixture.
Add the 2 cheeses and simmer for about 15 minutes. Serves 4-6 people.

title: ham 'n chicken chowder
directions: Cook ham in butter until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir often.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: bean pot
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Reserve drippings and saute onions until soft.
Stir in brown sugar, vinegar and salt.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Mix with beans in crock-pot and cook 4 to 5 hours, high to low.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Flake salmon in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add soup, rice, sherry, onion, lemon juice and water.
Mix well.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: provolone corn loaf
directions: Sprinkle 2 teaspoons cornmeal on the bottom and sides of a greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan; set aside.

title: swedish tea ring
directions: Add shortening, sugar and salt to scalded milk.
When cooled to lukewarm, add yeast and half the flour and beat well.
Let rise until light in a warm, draft-free place.
Add egg and remaining flour.
Mix well and let rise.
Roll dough into oblong strip about 1/4-inch thick and 13 x 9 inches.
Spread with melted butter, brown sugar, nuts and raisins.
Roll up like a jelly roll and form into a ring on a greased baking sheet.
With scissors make cuts two-thirds of the way through ring at 2-inch intervals.
Turn each cut section on its side.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake about 30 minutes in hot oven (375°).
Frost while hot with a thin icing made by combining the milk and confectioners sugar.

title: hawaiian loaf
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well.
Stir in banana.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, mix just until smooth.
Fold in pineapple and coconut.
Spoon into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: bacon cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup nuts, in a medium bowl.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight while shaped and wrapped in plastic wrap.
Roll in nuts and serve with crackers or bread sticks.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon-herb beef pot roast(sunday)
directions: Makes 12 to 14 servings. Preparation time: 10 minutes. Cooking time: About 2 1/2 to 2 3/4 hours.

title: egg and spinach casserole
directions: Pull crumbs from inside of bread and measure, packing lightly. Place in bowl the melted butter and crumbs, thoroughly mixing with 2 forks.
Wash fresh spinach several times to thoroughly wash. Drain well and cook in a small amount of water in covered saucepan until tender.
When done, drain thoroughly and chop fine.
Season with 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper to taste.
Place spinach in a well buttered casserole or shallow baking dish (not too large as this is a small recipe).
Make 2 depressions in spinach with a spoon.
Drop the raw eggs into these depressions.
Sprinkle eggs slightly with salt and pepper.
Heat milk and cheese until cheese is melted.
Season and pour cheese sauce slowly over the eggs and spinach.
Cover with the buttered bread crumbs and bake in a 375° oven for about 25 minutes.
If not brown at this stage, place under broiler to brown and serve.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: peanut butter chocolate cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients. Stir in moist ingredients; mix well. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking pan.

title: canadian christmas meat pie
directions: Slightly prebake pie shell.
Mix meats and brown with water and onion; stir occasionally until pinkness is gone.
Drain and save meat broth.
Mash potatoes; if dry, blend meat broth in.
Mix potatoes with meat until smooth.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add ground cloves, cinnamon and salt.
Pour mixture into prebaked shell; top with crust and seal edges.
Bake at 400° until top is golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature. Cream and gradually stir in drained, crushed pineapple until smooth. Add 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and seasoned salt. Chill mixture well. Form into a ball and roll in remaining cup of pecans. Chill until serving time. Garnish with twists of pineapple, cherries and parsley. Serve with crackers.

title: date nut muffins
directions: In saucepan, combine dates, water and baking soda. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and set aside to cool. Preheat oven to 350°. Grease two 12 hole muffin pans or use paper liners. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs. Add flour and salt, beating until just combined. On low speed, beat in date mixture, vanilla and nuts. Fill prepared muffin pans 3/4 full with batter and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until they test done with a toothpick. Yield: 2 dozen muffins.

title: funny cake
directions: Mix together the boiling water, cocoa and 1/2 cup sugar; stir well and pour into pie crust.
Combine the remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Pour this mixture into pie crust over chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: rosemary chess squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugars (except powdered sugar).
Beat in eggs, flour, pecans and rosemary.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Add mixture and bake at 325°, 45 minutes.
While cake is hot, rub with powdered sugar.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix 1 cup halved strawberries with 2/3 cup water, simmer on stove.
Blend in sugar, cornstarch and 1/3 cup water.
Cook until mixture is thick and clear.
Let cool.
Pout the remaining strawberries into the already prepared pie shell.
Cover these strawberries with the cooled glaze and top with Cool Whip.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: casserole potatoes
directions: Bring cream to a boil.
Add potatoes.
Cook until cream is absorbed.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Put in casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese together.
Add Jell-O and mix until blended well.
Add strawberries and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat mushroom soup and milk.
Add sour cream and chicken. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Melt margarine with water; add stuffing mix and optional mushrooms.
Spread over chicken mixture. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, nutmeg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until well mixed.
Sift together flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Combine drained pineapple and sour cream.
Add pineapple mixture alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.

title: jiffy coffee cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well.
Chill 2 hours.
Form into small balls and mash with potato masher or a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot fruit dish
directions: Drain
fruit (save juice except pineapple juice).
Save enough for 2 cups.
To juice add cornstarch, sugar, sherry and butter. Cook until thick.
Arrange fruit in Pyrex dish.
Pour mix over fruit.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: beaumont, texas dessert salad
directions: Combine dry gelatin and cottage cheese.
Fold in whipped topping and mix well.
Add oranges, nuts and pineapple, stirring gently!
Spoon into glass bowl.
Chill well.
Serves 8 - 10.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.
Can be reheated.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler.
When melted, remove from heat.
Add peanuts and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Put into refrigerator until hard.
Makes 3 dozen clusters.

title: chi-chi's cool salsa dip
directions: In a small bowl combine salsa, sour cream and cilantro.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot lettuce salad
directions: Place 2 cloves of garlic in one cup of vinegar and let it soak for 1 1/2 hours in a large glass jar with top.
After an hour and a half add the ingredients to this vinegar mixture.
Put a top on the jar and shake well; place in refrigerator.
This dressing will keep indefinitely.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cover bottom of an 8-inch square pan with fruit.
Mix 1/2 cup of sugar, butter, baking powder, salt, milk and flour; pour over fruit.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Add tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Simmer until thickened.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, place 2 to 3 tortillas to cover bottom of pan.
Mix together refried beans and 1/4 cup salsa.
Spread 1/2 of bean mixture over tortillas in pan.
Top with 1/2 ground beef mixture. Sprinkle 1/2 of both cheeses.
Add 2 or 3 more tortillas over cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Top with more tortillas and sprinkle with more cheese, if desired.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with sour cream, shredded lettuce, tomato, salsa or additional cheese, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: praline cookies
directions: Add sugar, nuts and vanilla to frothy egg white.
Drop by spoonfuls on a foil covered cookie sheet (mini cookies will require only 1/2 teaspoon).
Preheat oven to 400°.
Place cookies in oven.
Cut off heat and bake for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and allow cookies to cool on sheet before serving.
Yields about 30 cookies.

title: grandma's melting moments
directions: Stir together flour, cornstarch and sugar.
In a large bowl heat margarine until smooth.
Add flour mixture, slowly and add vanilla to margarine.
Beat until well blended.
Refrigerate one hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet 1 1/2-inches apart, flatten.
Bake in 375° oven 10 - 12 minutes. Cool.
While hot, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and mix thoroughly.
Add corn flakes and mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Cool.
This may be spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan and cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: bread sticks
directions: Cut each hot dog bun into 6 strips.
Melt margarine (if using garlic salt, add to margarine).
With paint brush, brush all sides of bread.
Sprinkle with sesame seed and poppy seed.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
These can be frozen.
You don't have to thaw before putting on serving dish.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese.
Add chopped pecans.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chili powder.
Decorate with pecan halves.
Chill until firm.

title: granny's summertime coolers
directions: Put enough ice to make about 1 quart of crushed ice in blender and crush well.
Add Kool-Aid and blend well.
Put in large cups or glasses.
Add a spoon and straw.
Adults and children enjoy Granny's Southern Heat Beaters.

title: chicken under foil
directions: On large sheet of aluminum foil, place all ingredients in center.
Wrap up ingredients and try to form good seal.
Repeat this process two more times, making sure to form good seals. Place chicken under foil directly in coals of fire.
Allow to cook 15 to 20 minutes on each side.
Take off fire and open carefully. Meal should be eaten directly from foil.
This recipe is for one person and provides a complete meal.

title: broccoli with stuffing
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.	Combine egg, onion,
soup
and mayonnaise.
Layer in 2 quart casserole dish broccoli,
cheese
and
small
amount
of
sauce.
Repeat layers. Top
with stuffing mix.
Sprinkle with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook on medium-low in large saucepan,
enough oil to cover the bottom, an onion and meat, until browned.
Add blended whole tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper and cook 30 minutes on low.
Add tomato paste, chicken broth and water.
Cook 3 hours on low.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Leaving mushrooms whole, bring to a boil in equal parts of vinegar and water.
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Drain and allow to cool.
In a glass bowl, place mushrooms with oil and spices.
Add a little vinegar to top.
Let set overnight.
Before serving, drain out a little of vinegar.

title: corn potpourri
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1 stick butter.
Place in well-greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Then melt and drizzle 1 stick butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: soy sauce flavored dip
directions: Mix together all the ingredients, adjusting the amount of flakes and soy sauce to your taste.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: You may substitute vegetables of your choice.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in well cleaned crab shells or baking dish in moderate oven about 20 minutes.

title: delish oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal in boiling water; let stand while you cream the butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Add creamed mixture and oatmeal mixture; beat well.
Add flour; mix well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl. Toss with cucumbers. Refrigerate.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Place in blender with water and chop. Drain and reserve 3 tablespoons liquid.
Heat liquid with gelatin until softened. Cool and add salt and pepper.
Add vegetables, mayonnaise, cream cheese and lemon juice. Good sandwich spread.

title: ponche(punch from latin america)
directions: Fill a blender container 3/4 full of crushed ice.
Add ingredients in the order listed and blend at high speed until foamy.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Place each chicken breast between 2 sheets of clear plastic wrap.
Pound with the flat side of a meat mallet to 1/4-inch thickness.
Remove plastic.
In a large skillet cook the mushrooms and green onions in 2 tablespoons of melted butter or margarine until just tender.
Remove from the skillet.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let rise for 1/2 hour.
Put in 2 bread pans.
Let rise for another 15 min. and put in preheated oven.
Bake at 350°F for 1 hour or until brown.

title: nana's special pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shells.
Chill about 2 hours.

title: ralston pineapple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins or use paper liners. Sift together flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir in Ralston.
Beat egg (or use egg substitute); add oil and pineapple and mix.
Add dry ingredients and stir until dry is moistened. Makes 12 muffins.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Slice peaches in crust.
Sprinkle 1/4 sugar mixture over peaches.
Add cream. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture over top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, at medium-high speed, beat margarines until creamy.
Gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg, vanilla and salt; beat until blended.
On low speed, a little at a time, mix in all but 1 tablespoon of the flour until just combined.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts and wrap each piece in plastic wrap.
Place in freezer 1 hour or in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours or until well chilled.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: vegetable appetizer pizza
directions: Cream together all the ingredients and spread over cooled dough.
Top with raw minced vegetables to your liking.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and a cut up tomato.
Dress with black olives after cutting into serving pieces.
Serve cold.

title: cabbage and sausage turkey dressing
directions: Cook sausage meat until well done, breaking it up with spoon. Chop celery, cabbage and onions up rather small and add to sausage meat.
Add about 8 to 10 ounces water and mix well, then cover and let simmer until vegetables are soft.
Stir occasionally.
Also add salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Let cool.
When cooled, add eggs and moistened bread.
Mix well and then stuff your turkey.

title: corn pone
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 375° until golden brown.

title: california chews(macadamia cookies)
directions: Mix in manner of chocolate chip cookies.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned; do not overcook.
Delicious!

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Salt well.
Top each chop with a lemon slice or 1 teaspoon of ReaLemon juice.
Sprinkle generously with brown sugar.
Pour 1 tablespoon ketchup over each chop.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours on 350°.

title: mocha log
directions: Roll cake up.
Frost outside also.
Make chocolate curls. Shave thin with a vegetable parer.

title: tim's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Pour into boiling water and cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until blended. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour slowly, beating well.
Add lemon extract and juice; blend.
Pour into greased angel food cake pan.
Cook at 300° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla with mixer.
Add eggs, beating until light and fluffy.
Add melted chocolate and blend well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with water to chocolate mixture.
Pour batter into three 8 or 9-inch pans which have been greased and lined with waxed paper.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Put layers together with date filling.
Frost with favorite fudge frosting.

title: smothered chops over rice
directions: Brown pork chops in oil in frying pan.
Place in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Mix together soup, water, catsup and Worcestershire sauce; pour over chops.
Cover and cook in 325° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: homemade maple syrup
directions: Bring to boil, then remove from heat.
Add maple flavoring to taste.
Do not refrigerate.

title: festive "holladay" pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare pastry.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in butter.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate morsels and walnuts.
Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake until set, about 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped or ice cream. Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: lynda's sweet and sour dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in the blender.

title: bologna soup
directions: Heat tomatoes; bring to a boil.
Add potatoes and salt to taste; reduce heat.
Fry bologna in oil until brown.
Add onion. Cook until tender.
Pour into tomatoes and potatoes.
Add black pepper.
Let simmer until potatoes are tender.
Good over rice and with cornbread.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat the butter.
Cook the onion and garlic.
Add the ground beef and cook until browned.
Stir in the tomato juice, tomato paste, Sugar Twin, salt, pepper and basil.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat, about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts. One-half cup serving contains 157 calories.
Great for diabetics.

title: cauliflower, broccoli and rice salad
directions: Drain and rinse rice well.
Clean vegetables and mix with rice in a large bowl.
In separate bowl, mix salad dressing and buttermilk mix together.
Pour over rice and vegetables and mix. Refrigerate.

title: navy soup bean
directions: Cook beans until tender (about 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Add potatoes, onion, carrots, garlic, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Good with Mexican cornbread and fresh cole slaw.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, egg and milk.
Cook over low heat; boil 1 minute.
Add butter, vanilla, rice and raisins.
Cool and serve.

title: "one meal casserole"
directions: Brown ground chuck and season to taste.
Pour off fat.
Mix soups and water.
Pour in meat.
Place Tater Tots in oblong casserole dish and pour meat mixture over Tater Tots.
Top with cheese.
Bake at least 30 minutes at 350°.

title: plain layer cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar well.
Add eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture with milk.
Blend well and add flavoring.
Bake at 350°.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving 1 tablespoon syrup.
Combine pineapple chunks, reserved syrup, mandarin orange sections, coconut, marshmallows and sour cream.
Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours.
Before serving, sprinkle with pecans.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Melt butter; add flour and blend.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Heat to boiling and cook 2 minutes.
Add corn, salt, pepper, sugar and cheese.
Fold beaten eggs into corn mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: beef with mushrooms
directions: Place oil, salt and pepper in a preheated, heavy 10-inch frying pan. Cut meat into thin slices and add onion and garlic. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until meat is brown. Add bouillon and mushrooms. Cover pan and cook over low heat for 10 minutes. Blend together cornstarch, soy and water.
Add to meat mixture. Cook a few minutes, stirring constantly, until juice thickens and mixture is very hot.
Serve with rice.
Enjoy!

title: conch patties
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients and form into patties.
Fry to golden brown in oiled pan (5-10 minutes).
Makes 6-9 patties.

title: best ever barbecues
directions: Combine all ingredients except hamburger in a saucepan.
Pull apart hamburger into small sections or balls and place into saucepan mixture.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Place chicken between 2 pieces of plastic wrap.
Pound chicken to 1/2-inch thickness.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; coat with flour.
In a large skillet, brown chicken in 3 tablespoons of butter over medium heat for about 5 minutes or until lightly golden.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Crunch up 1 roll of crackers; lay in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Melt butter; pour over crackers for crust.
Put broccoli in.
In saucer, mix milk and soup, then 1/2 the cheese. Pour over broccoli.
Slice other 1/2 cheese.
Put in chunks on top, then crush other 1/2 of crackers and put on top.
Put in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain
first 7 vegetables.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Cool
and
pour
over vegetables.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
When ready to serve, drain and reserve liquids for leftovers.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice in water.
In preheated frypan, cook oil (less oil if you have a nonstick pan).
Break egg in cup; beat with fork. Pour into warm oil; keep stirring until egg is stringy.
Cook about 1 minute.
Add cooked rice, green onions and tops and soy sauce.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn, eggs, sour cream, muffin mix and salt and put in a greased casserole dish.
Cut up stick of oleo and put on top. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put Mozzarella cheese on top and cook for 30 minutes more.

title: orange stuff salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dried orange jello together.
Stir in orange slices and crushed pineapple.
Stir in Cool Whip.
(I sometimes don't use all of carton, depends upon look and how well mixing up.)
Can be made in advance and refrigerated or eaten right then.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Cook rhubarb with sugar and water for about 10 minutes or until soft.
Serve over ice cream, pound cake, etc.

title: gingerbread pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco, molasses, eggs and sugar until fluffy; sift flour and spices together and add to molasses mixture and milk.
Bake in Bundt pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Glaze with a thin glaze of corn syrup (good with Cool Whip).

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients.
Put together; add milk and then blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: mixed berry jam
directions: Wash and drain berries; halve strawberries.
Add all berries to a large 6 to 8-quart saucepan.
Add pectin to berries and stir together.
Over high heat, bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Quickly add sugar.
Bring to a full, rolling boil and boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and skim foam.
Ladle into clean, hot 1/2-pint jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Wipe jar rims with damp cloth; apply new lids and ring bands.
Process in a simmering water bath for 10 minutes.

title: marshmallow yam casserole
directions: Blend yams with sugar, salt, spice, butter and cream.
Mix half the marshmallows with yams.
Turn into greased baking dish. Top with remaining marshmallows.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes, until mixture is puffy and marshmallows delicately browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cajun gumbo over rice
directions: Make a roux by adding heated bacon fat and adding flour. Brown slowly until the color of chocolate.
Set aside.
Saute onion and bell peppers in butter. Cut up sausage and crab meat. Combine all ingredients in a big pot.
Let heat, then stir in roux.
Cover and cook slowly for about 4 hours.
Add seasonings to taste.
Serve over rice.
As they say in the bayou, "Eat all you want and pass a good time."

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Soften cream cheese, beating in sugar and mayonnaise.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into loaf pan.
Freeze for at least 12 hours before serving.
Cover with aluminum foil before freezing.
Remove 1 hour from freezer before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugars, egg yolks (well beaten), flour, milk and then vanilla.
Add nuts and fold in beaten egg whites. Put in well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked apple french toast
directions: In skillet melt butter with sugar. Add apples and cook five minutes. Place apple mixture in a 9x13 pan. Cut cream cheese into cubes and place over apples. Sprinkle with dried cranberries. Top with bread cubes. Beat eggs, milk and vanilla. Pour over bread. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Place in refrigerator over night. Bake in morning at 350 degrees for 50-60 minutes. Let stand for 15 minutes before serving. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with warm maple syrup.

title: honey grilled spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine honey and Lea & Perrins Worcestershire sauce in a bowl.
Brush ribs on both sides with mixture.
Place ribs in a shallow baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes, basting twice with sauce.
Remove the ribs from the baking pan and grill 4 inches above medium-hot coals for about 30 minutes more, turning frequently and basting with sauce before each turn.
Start checking for doneness after 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cut between ribs.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Spread over cake while warm.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add raisins and caraway seed.
Add Crisco.
Beat 1 egg; add to dry ingredients, then add milk.
Mix together.
Bake in a 350° oven in greased pan for 1 hour until golden brown.
Makes 1 very large loaf or 2 (9 1/2 x 3 1/2-inch) pans.

title: chocolate chip krispies
directions: Mix in pan over low heat the margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
When melted, add marshmallows.
Heat slowly until marshmallows melt, then add Rice Krispies.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes, then cut into squares.

title: individual shepherd's pie
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions, except omit butter and substitute skim milk for milk; set potatoes aside.
In a mixing bowl, stir together vegetables, lamb, gravy and basil.
Divide among four 12 to 16-ounce casseroles.
Top each casserole with mashed potatoes and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until mixture is heated through.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk and egg yolks.
Cook in microwave (High heat) until thick, stirring occasionally with wire beater.
When thick, add vanilla, margarine and coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box. When done, let cool for 1/2 hour.
Mix glaze and strawberries together, spread on cake.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in pan.
Add tomato sauce and spices.
Simmer 10 to 20 minutes.
Add macaroni to mixture

title: hot pineapple eggnog
directions: Separate egg yolks and whites.
Beat yolks thoroughly in half the sugar.
Beat whites thoroughly in remaining half sugar.
Bring pineapple juice to a boil.
Add cream; reheat and pour over egg yolk mixture.
Fold egg whites into hot mixture.
Sprinkle with orange peel.
Serves 12.

title: fluffy french toast
directions: Beat flour, sugar, salt, milk and eggs with hand beater until smooth.
Soak bread in egg mixture until saturated.
Heat margarine in skillet until melted.
Cook bread until golden brown, about 12 minutes on each side.

title: frog eyed salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Cool mixture to room temperature.
Bring water, remaining 2 teaspoons salt and oil to boil.
Add acini de pepe.
Cook at rolling boil until acini is done.
Drain acini and rinse with cool water.
Drain again and bring to room temperature.

title: potato soup
directions: Chop onion.
Cut up potatoes.
Cook onion in fat in a large pan until tender.
Add water and potatoes.
Cover and boil gently until potatoes are done.
Partly mash potatoes with a fork without draining them.
Add milk, salt, vegetables and pepper.
Heat slowly, stirring to keep them from sticking.
Do not boil.
Makes 6 servings, 1 cup each.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Partially thaw out lemonade and Cool Whip, mix together until smooth.
Combine with Eagle Brand milk and softened cream cheese; pour into pie shells and refrigerate at least two hours.
Makes two pies.

title: petticoat tails
directions: Mix together well butter, sugar and flavoring.
Sift together and stir in flour and salt; mix thoroughly with hands.
Press and mold in long smooth roll about 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill until stiff (several hours or overnight in refrigerator).
With thin sharp knife, cut in thin slices and place a little apart in baking pan or ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until lightly brown in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
You may add chocolate chips or nuts or peanut butter and they keep so long.
They are very good.

title: tuna dill spread
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Use as sandwich filling or spread on crackers.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: swordfish steak by becky
directions: Mix all.
Place swordfish in marinade.
Store in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.
Turn steaks 1 or 2 times while cooking, 3 to 4 minutes each side.
(Mako shark can be substituted if swordfish is unavailable.)

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Cook in large saucepan; stir until margarine melts.
Cook to soft ball stage. Cool.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten egg; sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to the first mixture with the milk. Pour dough in a greased baking dish.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups drained cherries and 1 cup sugar.
Just before putting in oven, cover with 1 cup boiling water.
Bake for 45 minutes in moderate oven (350°).

title: nelia's rolls
directions: Mix salt and 4 1/2 cups flour.
Cut in flour and shortening. Mix flour mixture with other ingredients.
Knead 1/2 cup flour (or more if needed) into the mixture.
Let rise in a warm place.
Mash down.
Make out and place in pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: turkey burritos
directions: Brown ground turkey.
Add salsa and ketchup; set aside.
Warm tortillas.
On each tortilla layer turkey mixture, cheese, lettuce, sour cream and tomatoes.
Roll up and serve.
You may add rice and corn to the meat mixture or serve as a side dish.

title: chicken miracle
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Top with chipped beef. Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour onto chipped beef.
Sprinkle on frozen peas and chopped pimento.
Crumble bread cubes and add. Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Layer cream cheese, beans, sour cream, taco sauce and cheese 2 inches deep in a 9-inch dish.
Use cream cheese for bottom layer.

title: braised sirloin tip
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Stir in wine, consomme, onion salt, garlic and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Blend cornstarch in water; stir into meat mixture until it boils.
Simmer for 1 minute (you may need a little more cornstarch if thickness is not to your desire).
Serve over rice.

title: rodney's biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Add enough milk to hold it together.
Knead gently, but not too long.
Roll or pat out about 1/2-inch thick.
Lightly flour top of dough; fold half of dough over other half; press together a little.
Cut.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine with sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and flavorings alternately with sifted flour.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Saute pork chops in mixture of brown sugar, mustard, spices, juice, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook in frypan for 1 hour or until done.

title: cherry-o cream cheese pie
directions: Mix sugar and 1 heaping tablespoon flour together and add butter.
Blend until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla plus lemon peel.
Place in an unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° until knife comes out clean, about an hour.

title: shawn's meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, onion, pepper, ketchup and eggs.
Add bread cubes and work in.
Add salt and pepper.
Shape in an oval and place in "sprayed" pan.
Top with more ketchup.
Bake for 1 to 2 hours.
Let cool for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Keep pie shell refrigerated until ready for use.
Beat eggs in a medium sized bowl.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup, salt and vanilla.
Blend well.
Stir in butter and broken pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
If you like, make a design when placing the pecan halves on top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes in a preheated 375° oven.
Yields 8 servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Crumble brownies. Layer in trifle bowl as follows: brownies, pudding, Cool Whip and candy. Repeat.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix according to package directions, using soup and water for liquid called for.
Bake at 350° in either loaf or two 8-inch pans according to directions on package.
Ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: chili with corn dumplings
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in Dutch oven over medium heat until beef is brown, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain and return to Dutch oven. Drain and reserve 1/2 cup corn to use in Dumplings. Stir remaining undrained corn, tomatoes and next 3 ingredients into
beef mixture.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: frosting
directions: Scald milk.
Set aside to cool to slightly warm.
Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Stir in egg white.
Add milk to mixture, a little at a time, beating until smooth.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Drain.
Cook chicken, then chop into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Serve hot.

title: cauliflower-broccoli crunch
directions: Combine cauliflower, broccoli and onion.
Combine mayonnaise and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over vegetables. Toss gently; cover and chill.
Miracle Whip Lite and NutraSweet may be substituted for mayonnaise and sugar.
Makes a good low-calorie dish.
Yields 10 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook until thickened.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and 1 small can coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell; top with egg whites.

title: apple dumplings
directions: In a saucepan mix water, sugar and oleo.
Mix cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves before adding to mixture.
Bring to a rolling boil. Pour over apples after in pan.

title: annie's holiday corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in casserole dish (2-quart).
Top with crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clear.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Put milk, sugar, egg yolks, cornstarch and salt in double boiler and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and coconut.
When cool, pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake until browned.
Also good with graham cracker crust.

title: grandma fougerat's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture.
Roll into log.
Chill and slice to bake.

title: apricot cheese ball
directions: Mix first five ingredients together. Push into ball shape in bowl with wooden spoon. Refrigerate for 20 to 30 minutes, enough to stiffen slightly. Roll in chopped nuts.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add milk and slightly beaten egg yolks.
Beat all together.
Boil until thick in double boiler.
Add butter.
Remove from heat when thick and smooth.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Beat whites of eggs and add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Put on top of pie and brown in oven.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together, then flour, soda and melted oleo.
Add nuts. Roll in rolls about the size of half dollar and roll in wax paper. Place in refrigerator until chilled enough to slice thin.
Bake at 350°.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker pie shell. Refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together well and shape into a ball.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix together and put in greased square pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Cherry Sauce.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Boil, peel and grate potatoes.
Mix with other ingredients. Place in greased casserole.
Top with crumbs (cracker or corn flake crumbs may be used).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Casserole may be prepared and refrigerated overnight.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Cut up fruit of your choice.
Dip fruit in and enjoy!

title: waldorf salad(low-fat!)
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, toss together the chopped apples and lemon juice.
Stir in the raisins, grapes and celery.

title: manicotti bake
directions: Boil manicotti a few minutes to soften slightly.
Mix all ingredients and stuff into the manicotti.
Place into greased casserole.
Pour tomato sauce over the top and add more cheese. Cover with foil and bake until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with basil.

title: rye bowl
directions: Prepare the day before serving.
Chop corned beef into small pieces.
Mix with all other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: fiesta corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving or overnight.

title: peanut butter & jelly sandwich
directions: Put together and eat it.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Add egg yolk, milk and vanilla. Gradually mix in flour.
Chill batter until dough can easily be formed into small balls.

title: senator russell's potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla and butter.
Beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into buttered casserole.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Add salt and pepper (to taste), drain.
Add tomatoes, sauce and chili beans.
Add chili powder (to taste).
Simmer until thickened.

title: mock pizza
directions: Spread cream cheese on plate, then spread the chili sauce. Slice the ham into bite-size pieces.
Slice pepperoni.
Place onto chili sauce.
Sprinkle with bacon bits, then add Mozzarella cheese.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Cut chicken up in small pieces.
Mix noodles, chicken, mushroom soup and milk.
Add mushrooms.
Place in casserole dish and top with mein noodles.
Bake until brown on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add flour, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Cook slowly until thickened. Add chicken breast.
Set aside.
Make crust.

title: swedish nut cake(yields 1 cake)
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheddar zucchini supreme
directions: Melt margarine in medium size skillet.
Add zucchini, salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 1/2 cup cheese; stir until melted.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave red, white and blue cake
directions: Prepare cake according to instructions using only egg whites and water.
Pour mixture into microwave-safe Bundt pan, lightly oiled.
Microwave cake on High 4 minutes.
Turn cake.
Microwave on Medium-high 8 to 10 minutes until cake begins to pull away from pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Invert onto cake plate and cool.
Cut cooled cake in half.
Spoon cherry filing on bottom layer.
Add 1/2 of whipped topping on top of cherry filling.
Place top layer of cake on and spoon blueberry pie filling over top layer.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and whole cherries.

title: lazy cabbage rolls
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Drain well.
Combine other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender, tomato juice is cooked down and mixture is thick.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt margarine in 8 inch square pan. Spread brown sugar on bottom of pan. Arrange pineapple on top and place a cherry half in each hollow. In a bowl stir shortening to soften. Sift in flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add syrup, lemon peel and egg. Mix until all flour is dampened, beat for 2 minutes. Pour batter over pineapple. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Let cake stand in pan for 10 minutes and invert on plate. Serve warm with whipped cream or best with ice cream.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Cream butter; add eggs, cake mix and oranges.
Mix well.
Bake three (9-inch) layer cake pans at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: fingerfood dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add green onion dip mix and blend well. Add milk, a little at a time, to this mixture until smooth and creamy (about the consistency of whipped cream).
Place in a small bowl in the middle of a platter.
Arrange veggies around it.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Heat oil on medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook for about 1 minute, stirring.
Add vegetables and stir until crisp and tender.
Add pineapple and heat.
Serve over rice.

title: cranberry waldorf
directions: Grind cranberries. Combine with marshmallows and sugar.
Cover and chill overnight. Add apples, grapes, pecans and salt.
Mix well. Fold in whipped cream and chill. Serve in a large bowl.

title: brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas first and then add other ingredients.
Mix well. Bake for 50
minutes
in
a
12-inch Dutch oven with 10 coals on top and 8 on bottom.

title: casserole
directions: Put browned beef in casserole dish.
Add soups and water. Spread cheese over meat and soups.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Begin adding milk and flour alternately.
When you have added about half of the milk and flour, add half of the egg whites which have been beaten until stiff enough to hold a peak.
Add balance of milk and all flour except 1/2 cup which is reserved to add following addition of remaining egg whites at the last.
Bake as any other layer cake.
This makes 3 large layers or 4 small ones.

title: pizza dough
directions: In a large bowl combine 1 1/4 cups of flour, yeast and salt. Add water and yeast.
Beat until well blended.
Using a spoon, mix in as much of the remaining flour as you can.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead 6 to 8 minutes.
Divide in half.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Roll out to make two 12-inch pizzas.
Top and cook in a 425° oven for 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together, then add all other ingredients, alternating flour with the milk.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy crab dip
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add crabmeat, then salsa and other condiments.
Serve with fresh nachos or Melba rounds.

title: lima cheese bake
directions: Pour boiling water over frozen lima beans.
Break the beans apart; drain.
Blend the soup and milk together and add the limas to the mixture, along with the celery and the parsley.
Stir in 1/2 the fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Garnish with remaining onions and bake for another 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix butter, cocoa, shortening and Coke in saucepan and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows.
When marshmallows are melted, place all remaining ingredients in mixing bowl.

title: roast loin of pork
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle pork on both sides with salt, pepper and thyme.
Make 4 gashes in top of loin and insert one sliver of garlic into each gash.
Put pork in roasting pan and place onions in halves around the loin.
Place in oven and bake for 30 minutes.
Pour off fat and add wine and broth.
Return to oven at 375°.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs well and add to butter and sugar.
Sift (in separate bowl) 3/4 cup flour with 1/2 teaspoon baking powder.
Fold into butter mixture.
Add flavoring.
In separate bowl, mix nuts and fruit, then cut up in small pieces with 1 cup flour.
Last, add fruit and nuts and blend well.
Put in a cold oven, then turn on at 250° and bake 3 hours.

title: s'mores bars
directions: Make brownie mix as directed on package.
When it is all done cooking, shut off oven and close door so it stays warm.
Sprinkle the mini marshmallows over the top of brownie mix and the cups of morsels, also.
Set in warm oven for about 3 minutes; take out of oven.
Take graham crackers in whole pieces and press on top of mixture.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: meatballs
directions: On low, heat the grape jam and barbecue sauce until the jam is dissolved. Pour over the meatballs and cook on low until thoroughly heated.

title: iced tea
directions: Put 3 cups of water in a pan with tea bags.
Bring to a boil. Put 1 cup of sugar in a 1 gallon pitcher; pour boiled water in pitcher.
Add water until full.
Stir.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: perfect pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 or 40 minutes longer or until knife comes out clean.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat with onion and celery.
Drain, then add all other ingredients as given.
Salt and pepper to taste; doesn't take much, then add oregano to taste.
Put in slow cooker on medium and is ready in no time.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread nuts and coconut on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Soften margarine and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Pour over cake mix evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake is done.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef. Mix beef, cream of mushroom, milk and French fried onions together. Put in large greased casserole dish. Put green beans on top. Then top with Tater Tots. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: asparagus bisque
directions: In large saucepan, combine asparagus, onions, broth, water, butter and lemon pepper seasoning.
Cook over medium heat until onions are tender.
This will probably take about 10 minutes. Combine flour and 1/4 c. milk.
Whisk until smooth.
Stir into soup.
Add remaining milk or cream.
Simmer for about 5 minutes. Process in blender or food processor until smooth.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine and mix or just layer ingredients except chips and dressing.
Add these just before serving.
Serves a crowd.
Keep covered in refrigerator.

title: whole wheat cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix wet ingredients in a separate, large bowl.
Fold dry ingredients into wet ingredients.
Pour mixture into oiled pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate-covered peanut butter balls
directions: Put 2 pounds of sugar in a bowl; add melted butter and peanut butter.
Mix with hands until thoroughly mixed.
Roll into balls. Set in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, melt chocolate; dip balls or pour over.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Enjoy.

title: klondike candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and cream until it reaches a temperature of 238°, almost a hard ball.
Pour over mixture of cornflakes, Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts.
Mix very thoroughly and spread on greased cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces and enjoy.

title: mexican salsa dip
directions: In 2-quart casserole, layer cream cheese, avocado, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, 1 cup salsa, 1 cup onion, 1 cup salsa and 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until cheese is melted and bubbling.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cooked squash, soup, onion, cheese, beaten eggs and cracker crumbs. Pour into a casserole dish. Top with additional crushed cracker crumbs and dot thoroughly with oleo. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: colcannon potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes; cut each into quarters.
In 1/2 inch boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt, in medium saucepan, cook potatoes, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes, or until fork-tender and completely cooked.
Drain.
Return pan to low heat, shaking to dry potatoes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flavoring and graham cracker crumbs, mixing well.
Stir in pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and eggs. Beat until fluffy. Sift together flour, salt and spices; add alternately with hot applesauce and soda. Finally, fold in nuts and raisins. Bake in well greased pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix together ingredients until it becomes play dough consistency.
Roll and cut into shapes with a cookie cutter.
Make a hole in the top of ornament and let dry for 3-5 days, uncovered. Turn over and dry another 1 1/2 days.

title: dump-in tuna bake
directions: Dump all ingredients into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinated fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice (1 cup of juice needed; add water if not full).
Cook juice and pudding until thick.
Drain peach slices.
Add 1/2 juice from oranges to the pudding.
Mix with pineapple, peaches and oranges.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Before serving, add lots of banana slices and strawberries.

title: party chicken salad
directions: Combine salad ingredients; chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Garnish with olives, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chop in iron skillet in small amount of salad oil. Drain green beans and save liquid.
Place green beans on top of pork chops.
Add 1/2 soup can of green bean liquid to cream of celery soup.
Mix well and pour over pork chops and green beans. Cover and bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place crescent rolls in a casserole dish.
Brown sausage; drain and sprinkle over rolls.
Mix 6 to 8 eggs; add little milk and pour over sausage.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: breakfast bran muffins
directions: Grease tins.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate. Batter will last
up to 6 weeks. When ready to bake, add nuts, raisins or dates.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients, then add to 1 pound of cooled macaroni.
Add 6 eggs, onion, celery and carrots (diced).

title: instant pudding cookies
directions: Make into balls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: mud hens
directions: Cream butter and white sugar together.
Add 1 whole egg and 1 egg yolk, beaten together, to mixture.
Blend in dry ingredients and vanilla.
Spread this into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: pesto bow tie pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Cool.
Add Pesto sauce, pimentos, olives and Parmesan cheese.
Mix gently, but thoroughly.
Serve chilled.

title: blender ketchup
directions: Quarter tomatoes; remove stem ends.
Add peppers, seeded and cut in strips and onions, peeled and quartered.
Mix.
Put vegetables in blender container, filling jar 3/4 full.
Blend at high speed 4 seconds; pour into large kettle.
Repeat until all vegetables
are blended.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift the flour.
Measure and resift 3 times with sugar and salt.
The last time sift directly into a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening (at room temperature), eggs and 1/2 cup milk.
Stir with a spoon to blend.
Beat with an electric mixer, using low speed or by hand with a wooden spoon for 20 minutes by the clock.
Scrape sides of the bowl twice during beating.
Add the combined vanilla, melted and cooled chocolate, soda, water and the remaining milk. Beat 2 minutes more.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring cornstarch, sugar, water and syrup to a boil.
Stir in Jell-O.
Set aside to cool (20 to 30 minutes).
When cool, place the strawberries in pie shell and cover with Jell-O mix.
Chill until set.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: kava's cooler(herbal punch)
directions: Bring one-quart of water and ginger to boil.
Boil until you can smell the ginger.
Remove from heat.
In the same water, steep the peppermint and zinger teas for 20 minutes.
Strain.
Add sweetener and citric acid.
Refrigerate for tea or freeze to make popsicles.

title: coconut oatmeal crispies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugars. Add eggs and beat in vanilla. Combine oats, flour, coconut, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture. Shape into two 6-inch rolls. Wrap each in plastic wrap. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: roasted eggplant and red pepper terrine
directions: Roast the peppers.
Remove the skin and seeds.
Peel and slice the eggplant into 1/4-inch thickness.
Flour the slices.
Brown the eggplant slices in the oil; towel dry (to remove the oil). Oil a 6 x 4-inch terrine mold and rub garlic around its interior. Season the inside with salt and pepper.
Lay on layer of eggplant and cover with a layer of red pepper.
Season and add parsley and basil leaves.
Add layer of Chevre slices.
Continue to make layers until the terrine is completely filled.
Press and refrigerate the terrine for 4 hours.
Remove and slice.
Serve at room temperature.

title: swedish chicken
directions: Remove skin and excess fat from chicken.
Melt margarine. Grease sides and bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan generously.
Put cheese, salt, pepper and Bisquick in a bowl and toss thoroughly to coat the cheese.
Dip chicken in melted margarine and roll it in the cheese and Bisquick mixture.
Place in the pan with several pieces of cheese tucked around each piece of chicken.
Sprinkle remaining Bisquick and cheese over top of chicken.
Pour remaining margarine on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove foil and bake until browned and crisp on top, approximately 35 to 45 minutes more.

title: sliced dill pickles
directions: Put 2 or 3 slices of onion in a jar with small piece of garlic and half fill the jar with unpeeled cucumber slices, about 4 slices to an inch.
Add 2 or 3 more slices of onion and fill with cucumber slices.
Put more garlic and a head of fresh dill on top. (Make solution of these ingredients.)

title: pear crisp
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spread evenly the pears.
In a mixing bowl, mix with fingers the rest of the ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over pears.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
(Don't overbake as it will be dry.)
Serve warm with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: garlic spareribs
directions: Mix brown sugar, soy sauce, water, dry mustard and garlic powder and put over ribs in crock-pot; simmer all day.
Before serving, add cornstarch.
Serve with rice.

title: pecan crunchies
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco, brown sugar and vanilla together.
Add eggs and beat well. Add dry ingredients, then pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Lightly brown the onion in the butter.
Add the washed and chopped herbs.
Stir and steam for about 1 minute. Add the bouillon carefully and cook for 10 minutes. Remove from the heat. Combine the egg yolks and cream and add this mixture to the soup. Cube the bread slices.
Brown them in the butter and then add them to the prepared soup.

title: hawaiian drive-in burgers
directions: Form beef into 4 patties.
Place in shallow pan.
Blend soy sauce, sugar, garlic and ginger.
Pour on and marinate at least 30 minutes.
Broil, basting with marinade and serve on buns.

title: patio beans
directions: Fry sausage and chop into desired size.
Mix all other ingredients and bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add butter or margarine; cut into flour to make fine crumbs.
Add raisins and caraway seed.
Make a well in the center and add buttermilk.
Mix to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a floured board and knead for 1 minute.
Pat or roll out to a circle 1 1/2-inches thick.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Make a deep cross in center with a floured knife.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 425°.

title: brown onion sauce
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Stir in flour; add soup gradually.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Add flavorings.
Makes 2 cups.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover 12 to 14-inch pizza pan with foil.
Cut cookie dough into 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange over foil and press together.
Bake 10 minutes, until golden.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese with sugar and spread over top.
Mix brandy, vanilla and apricot preserves and heat until boiling. Place fruit on cream cheese and pour apricot mixture over all. Chill.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers mixed with the butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meringue frosting
directions: Beat the egg whites until peaks form.
Add the sugar, gradually beating in until stiff, but not dry.
Spread over top and sides of cake.
Place in oven and turn off the heat at once.
Let stand in oven with door closed for 3 hours.
Cool.

title: low-fat potato pancakes
directions: Boil potatoes until almost soft; peel and shred.
Blend remaining ingredients (except Butter Buds) and add to potatoes. In nonstick skillet, put in Butter Buds (half at a time).
Spoon in 1/3 cup potato mixture per pancake and cook 5 to 6 minutes, turning once.
Can be served with applesauce.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Bake a 9-inch pie shell and cool. Soften gelatin in cold water. Combine in top of double boiler sugar, salt, finely grated lemon rind and boiling water. Add softened gelatin and three well beaten egg yolks. Cook over boiling water until mixture coats a metal spoon (8 to 10 minutes). Stir constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in lemon juice. Pour into a bowl and chill for about 1 hour in refrigerator until it will mold slightly. Stir occasionally. Beat three egg whites to soft peaks. Gradually beat in sugar. Fold the meringue into cooled gelatin mixture. Pile into the baked, cooled 9-inch pie shell. Chill for 2 to 3 hours or until firm. If gelatin mixture becomes too thick for chiffon filling you can beat it until frothy before adding the meringue mixture.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Pare eggplant and cut into 1 inch cubes.
Boil with onions and 1 tsp salt until tender, but not mushy, about 5 minutes and drain.
Spread half crumbled crackers in buttered 10 x 6 x 2 glass baking dish.
Arrange eggplant and onions on top.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Top with remaining crackers and pour milk into corners to cover bottom of dish.
Drizzle butter over top.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 375 degrees in oven.

title: asparagus-tuna mold
directions: Mix tuna, onion and pepper.
Put gelatin in 1/4 cup water to dissolve.
Heat soup.
Add gelatin.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into greased fish mold.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Sprinkle with onion salt and celery salt.

title: frothy orange drink
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender.

title: easy mousse
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill at least one hour before serving.

title: peanut butter dip
directions: Mix peanut butter, water, lemon juice and orange juice.
Add yogurt and vanilla extract.
Stir until smooth.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with sliced fruits and vegetables.

title: "quickie" pickles
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and cover with ice cubes for 1 hour.
Drain.
Add to vinegar, sugar and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Pour in jars and seal.
May use in 24 hours.
If the cucumbers are seedy, cut the seeds out and slice in strips lengthwise.

title: coconut macaroon cookies
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir in whites of eggs and almond extract; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Garnish with candied cherry halves, if desired.

title: peanut butter slices
directions: Mix together until texture is stiff not sticky.
If it is sticky, add more sugar.
Take wax paper and spread out on table. Roll mixture out flat.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar heavily all over.
Start rolling dough up, keeping roll tight.
Refrigerate until firm, then cut 1/4-inch thick.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine sugar and oil, beat until smooth.
Add eggs, beat until smooth.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
When well mixed, fold in Raisin Bran.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Keeps 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: grandpa beans
directions: Brown hamburger, adding finely chopped onions before meat is completely done.
Add beans.
Add vinegar and Worcestershire sauce (catsup, salt and pepper to taste).
Turn heat down and let simmer 15 to 30 minutes.

title: orange coconut muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flours, wheat germ, sugar, coconut, baking soda and salt.
In small bowl, combine sour cream, eggs and oranges.
Stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Spoon into paper lined muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients except broccoli in a large bowl.
Add broccoli to mixture gently.
Pour in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple bavarian
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and chill to thicken slightly.
Fold Cool Whip into gelatin. Combine pineapple and sugar; fold into gelatin mixture.

title: sticky bun ring
directions: Grease Bundt pan well.
Distribute rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with pudding mix, nuts and cinnamon.
Heat oleo and sugar to boiling.
Pour over rolls.
Cover and let rise overnight at room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then invert on plate.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and drain the spinach. Tear into bite size pieces.
Beat or blend the oil, sugar, vinegar, onion, salt and dry mustard until thick and sugar is dissolved.
Fry the bacon until crisp; drain and crumble. Chop the eggs.
Pour dressing over all and let stand 30 minutes. Toss and serve.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill until serving time.
Makes 75 servings.

title: mustardy fried chicken breasts
directions: Wipe chicken breasts with damp paper toweling.
Sprinkle with the salt and black pepper.
In a bowl, beat together egg and mustard.
In separate bowl, combine Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs, mixing well.
Dip each chicken breast in egg mixture. Then roll in cheese mixture until evenly coated.
Lay chicken on waxed paper and allow coating to set for about 10 minutes.
Saute chicken on both sides in heated oil for 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Arrange on serving platter.
Sprinkle with green pepper slices and garnish with parsley sprig.

title: vienna coffee
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: apple-cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add cold water and pineapple, stirring well.
Chill mixture. When
mixture begins to thicken, add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Place mixture in a 9 x 13-inch dish and chill until firm.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Combine
cheese, butter, milk and mustard.
Toss potato chips and flour together.
Add to cheese mixture.
Form small round wafers.
Bake
at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 36 to 40 wafers.

title: favorite soup recipe
directions: Cook stew meat until tender.
Brown hamburger meat.
Remove all fat possible.
Add water as necessary.
Add other ingredients. Simmer 2 hours or more.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: First, scald milk and dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup warm water. Let milk cool to lukewarm, then add sugar, yeast and enough flour to make a thick batter.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Then add salt, shortening and enough flour to make a dough that can be handled easily.
Put in greased bowl and let rise (double), then make into rolls.
Let rise again and bake at medium 350° until brown.
These will keep in refrigerator for several days or can be frozen to be baked when needed (must make into rolls before freezing).

title: egg soup
directions: Beat eggs.
Add a little flour.
(Sprinkle in.)
Beat until lump free.
Pour egg mixture slowly into broth.
Stir slowly to keep from lumping.
Boil slowly, constantly stirring.

title: tuna-noodle quickie
directions: Cover bottom of casserole with dry noodles.
Mix milk and soup together and pour 1/2 of it over noodles.
Scatter tuna over this and add remaining 1/2 soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low calorie dip
directions: Combine and serve on baked potatoes.

title: susan's toffee bars
directions: Cream together sugars, shortening, vanilla, salt and eggs. Add flour and oats.
Spread batter in a greased
15 x 10 x 1 inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mother wineman's world famous rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan. Beat egg and combine remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Place crumbly mixture on top of rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Chopped walnuts are a tasty addition to the topping.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour and add to beaten eggs.
Add vanilla, buttermilk and melted butter.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° to 375° for 40 minutes.

title: microwave taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on dish with sides.
Spread chiles with liquid over top of cream cheese.
Next, layer Hormel chili and then a layer of Monterey Jack cheese.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Put wax paper over top.
Serve with taco chips.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
To juice, add cornstarch and mix well.
Heat until thickened.
Add crushed pineapple and mix.
Set aside and cool.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk and thawed, undiluted lemonade well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust and chill.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add milk, flour, baking powder and mix well.
Put batter in greased pan and pour sauce over it.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cold artichoke and wild rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: orange jello
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water; pour into blender. Add cream cheese to blender.
Mix orange juice, marshmallows, cottage cheese, pineapple, and cool whip.
Fold in with jello mixture.
Chill.

title: bobbie parson's georgia pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup and sugar and cook on medium heat until thick (the consistency of Karo syrup at room temperature).
Remove from heat. Add butter cut into chunks and allow to melt.
Beat eggs in mixing bowl and pour hot mixture over beaten eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour all into shell and bake at 325° until golden brown (center will be set, not shaky like jello) for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Boil oleo, oil, cocoa and water.
Sift flour and sugar.
Pour chocolate sauce over and mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking powder and vanilla. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts to flour mixture.
Melt butter; add brown sugar to melted butter. Mix well.
Add eggs to dry ingredients and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: hot pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour over pretzels.
Toss well; put into large roasting pan.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours.
Stir often.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and roll into balls.
Place on waxed paper on a cookie sheet and refrigerate.
Place chocolate and paraffin in double boiler and melt.
Lower heat.
Place toothpick in candy balls and dip in chocolate.
Twirl toothpick to remove.
Drop onto waxed paper; refrigerate to set chocolate. Yields 5 dozen (60 pieces at 1 tablespoon drops).

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and other ingredients.
Form into a ball and enjoy.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add beaten egg, vanilla and sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and diced apples.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and bake at 250° for about 45 minutes. Serve warm or cold, with or without whipped cream or ice cream.

title: marbled cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt butter; stir in cocoa.
Add powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.
Stir until smooth and frost brownies.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Place melted margarine in a baking dish. Mix sugar, milk and flour.
Pour on top of margarine.
Put peaches on top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Prepare a 9-inch unbaked pastry shell, line with sliced peaches.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Beat eggs until thickened.
Add sugar and beat well.
Stir in soft oleo. Pour over peaches and return to oven.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: deb's funnel cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix egg and milk and add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Add more milk, if too thick. Fill pan with 1-inch oil and heat.
Hold finger over bottom of a funnel.
Pour about 1/4 cup of batter into the funnel.
Remove your finger and let the batter drop in a spiral motion into the hot oil.
Fry until golden brown; turn once while cooking with tongs.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or your favorite fruit.

title: crock pot chili
directions: Put all ingredients in crock pot.
Cook on low for 6 - 8 hours. 30 minutes before serving, turn to high, remove cover and add 6-12 oz. tomato paste to thicken.
Keep cover off.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix well sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add water slowly.
Mix well. Bring to boil.
Add margarine.
Lower heat and cook 8 minutes. Stir constantly.
Let cool.

title: mayonnaise muffins
directions: Mix flour, milk, egg and mayonnaise in a bowl.
Grease and flour muffin pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full. Bake for 25 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot with butter.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: lentil soup
