directions: Rinse lentils. Put into cold water with all other ingredients and simmer for 2 hours until tender.

title: wrapped up apples
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt.
Add milk.
Dough will be like pie crust.
Set aside until apples are peeled.
Take half of dough and roll out to 9 x 13-inch rectangle.
Place sliced apples, half of sugar, cinnamon and butter mixture onto dough.
Roll into 4 x 13-inch shape and seal.
Put in half of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat for second roll.
Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Grease casserole (use 3 square size casserole). Mix soups and rice and water; set aside.
Place chicken pieces in casserole.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Melt together shortening and sugar.
Cool before adding eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Add chips and nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Do not overbake.

title: orange fruit cake
directions: Squeeze juice from oranges and stir in 3/4 cup sugar.
Remove loose fibers from orange peel and grind with nuts and raisins through medium grinder.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream shortening and remaining 1 1/2 cups sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla to buttermilk and stir in alternately with dry ingredients.
Bake at about 325° for half hour and then reduce heat slightly for another half hour.
Immediately upon removing from oven, dip orange juice and sugar over tops of cakes and cool in pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend first three ingredients until well mixed; fold in nuts, if desired.
Dip apple slices or other fresh fruit into the dip and enjoy!

title: cherry-date nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs. Add buttermilk. Mix in dry ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 2 loaves.

title: cajun wings
directions: Mix all together.
Fry chicken wings.
Put into sauce, put on baking sheet.
Bake in oven.
Makes 12 pounds.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot and cook over low heat until noodles are fully cooked, approximately 30 minutes. The less water you use, the more like chicken and dumplings this will be.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Heat cocoa, sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and quick oats.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheets or waxed paper.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and set aside on a paper towel to dry.
Mix flour, corn flour or fish fry, salt, cayenne pepper and garlic powder in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix egg, milk and creole mustard until completely blended.
Add 1/4 cup dry mixture to egg mixture and whisk until totally blended.
Heat oil until approximately 350 degrees.
When oil is hot, dip mushrooms into egg mixture and then into dry mixture.
Shake excess and fry until brown.

title: raisin custard pie
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add vinegar, vanilla, eggs and raisins. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until done, about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: To have a successful life, you must cultivate your own garden, planting as follows:

title: mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In bowl, beat brown sugar, butter and vanilla until creamy.
Add egg; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in 1 1/2 cup morsels and nuts.
Spread into foil-lined 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 23 to 25 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle 2/3 cup morsels over the top.
When morsels are shiny, spread evenly.
Chill for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: michigan rocks
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix together flour, cinnamon, salt, vanilla and baking soda in a little hot water.
Add dates and nutmeats.
Bake at 350° to 375°.

title: stuffed shell macaroni
directions: Cook shells.
Set aside.
Heat oil.
Add onion.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add garlic; cook 1 minute.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese and eggs.
Stir in parsley, Mozzarella, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stuff each shell with 1 tablespoon cheese mixture.
Spoon 1/2 cup sauce in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange shells over sauce in one layer.
Spoon remaining over shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf(e-z spiced)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: orange-sugar coated pecans
directions: Boil
sugar
with water, adding only 3 teaspoons orange juice and
grated
rind.
Add
salt.
Stir
in
pecan
halves, coating each
well before transferring to a buttered platter. Continue to stir until the nuts dry and separate.
Store in an airtight container when cool.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and salt and pepper. Chop almonds, celery, grapes and chicken.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over chicken.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: candied popcorn
directions: Combine popcorn and peanuts in a lightly greased roasting pan; mix well.
Melt butter in a saucepan; stir in brown sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in soda, salt and vanilla.
Pour mixture over popcorn; stir until coated.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.
Cool; store in an airtight container.

title: healthy candy
directions: Wash hands and apples.
Cut apples into sections.
Place apple slices into frying pan; cover with cider.
Cover pan and bring to a boil.
Simmer until apples are soft.
Cool.
Place small amounts of cooked apples into a food mill or ricer and grind. Add sugar and cinnamon to taste.

title: frosted brownies
directions: Brownies:
Cream 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup sugar.
Beat in eggs and chocolate syrup.
Gradually add flour.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 350°.
Before cool, ice.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as package directs. Drain.

title: speedy taco bake
directions: Cook beef and onion until brown; drain.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix seasoning, tomato sauce and drained corn.
Pour over beef.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook beans as directed on package. Drain well.
In a 1-quart casserole, combine beans with mushroom soup, bean sprouts and add water chestnuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream
together
the margarine and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add vanilla and dry ingredients with chocolate syrup.
Mix well. Pour into greased 13 x
9-inch
pan.
Bake
at
350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with Chocolate Fudge Frosting.

title: apricot fold-overs
directions: Cream butter and cheese until light.
Blend sifted flour into creamed mixture.
Add water and mix well.
Chill 4 to 5 hours. Meanwhile, cook dried apricots according to package directions. Drain well.
Stir sugar into hot fruit; cook and stir until mixture boils and becomes smooth; cool.
Divide chilled dough in half. Roll each half to 10-inch square; cut 2 1/2-inch squares.
Place 1 teaspoon apricot filling in each square.
Bring up diagonal corners and seal.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, water and seasonings.
Press onto 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan 1-inch thick.
Refrigerate until cold.
Cut into squares.
Roll in flour and brown in skillet.
Put squares in casserole.
Pour soup over (do not dilute soup).
Bake covered in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry waldorf gelatin
directions: In medium bowl, pour boiling water over gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts.

title: avocado-crab dip
directions: Mix diced avocado with lemon juice, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in cream cheese, sour cream and salt.
Add crabmeat and mix thoroughly.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: southwest shrimp cocktail
directions: Blend all ingredients well. Lightly toss with shrimp. Serve in small cups and/or with crackers.

title: pasta salad
directions: Chop up tomatoes, bell pepper, zucchini, squash, celery, onion, cucumber, carrots and artichoke hearts.
Set aside.
Cook pasta until done.
Toss in chopped vegetables.
Mix through bottle of dressing.
Top with bacon bits and parsley flakes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press Crescent rolls into square cookie sheet.	Bake till lightly brown.
Cool.
Mix together mayonnaise, cream cheese and ranch mix.	Spread over cooled Crescent rolls.
Wash and pat dry all veggies.
Shred or chop into small pieces.
Sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Refrigerate. Serve chilled.
Serves 10-12.

title: hobo cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening. Add eggs, vanilla and cream of tartar.
Add flour with dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoonful and flatten with fork. Bake at 300°.

title: bakeless fruit cake(the grace eidson family's favorite)
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and press firmly in pan lined with wax paper.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator (or longer).
Turn out, slice and serve with whipped cream topped with a cherry.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Drain fruit.
Arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter or margarine; add sugar and curry powder. Add juices from cans of fruit to this mixture and pour over fruit. Bake for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: shrimp spread mold
directions: Heat tomato soup (do not boil).
Dissolve cream cheese in soup.
Stir with wire whisk to blend.
Remove from heat and pour in the gelatine.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients to the soup.
Stir well. Pour into lightly oiled mold or serving container.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight. Serve with crackers, rye bread rounds or toast.

title: chicken dorito casserole
directions: Debone and chop chicken.
Saute onion in butter.
Add cream of chicken soup, chilies and cumin.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add chopped chicken.
Cover baking dish with Doritos.
Pour in mixture.
Cover with Doritos and grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: randi's beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add rest of ingredients, except 1 package of cooked noodles.
Layer noodles, meat mixture and Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs; mix well. Add all other ingredients. Pour into the pie shells, 1/2 mixture into each one. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in the middle comes out clean. Cool before serving. Makes 12 servings. Preparation time: 1:00.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix and pour in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix and add salad dressing to bind together.
A little lemon juice can be added to keep apples from turning brown.

title: "1973" old fashioned red devil's food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Put the first 4 ingredients in blender.
Cover and run on high for 20 seconds.
Sift remaining ingredients into mixing bowl, then add liquid mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Pour batter into prepared cake pans and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool on racks.

title: crunchy corn dogs
directions: You will need 12 skewers.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix beans, onion and pepper.
In a small bowl, blend remaining ingredients together and pour over beans.
Refrigerate 12 hours.

title: almond orange garden salad
directions: To make dressing: Combine first 4 ingredients in a jar and shake.

Combine almonds and sugar in skillet; cook over medium heat stirring until almonds are browned. Transfer to foil to cool. Tear lettuce into bite size pieces, place in salad bowl; add onions and oranges.
Pour on dressing; add pepper and toss. Top salad with almonds and parsley.
You will not need all of the dressing, use a little at a time.
This can be made a day ahead; but do not add dressing mix, almonds and parsley until ready to serve. Almonds will keep in zip lock bag 3 to 4 days.

title: mexicale zucchini
directions: Heat oil.
Add zucchini, carrot, onion, celery, pepper and herbs.
Cook covered over medium heat about 5 minutes until vegetables are done, but crisp.
Stir occasionally.
Add tomatoes and salsa.

title: blintz torte
directions: Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff.
Spread over cake mixture.
Sprinkle crushed walnuts over mixture.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and marshmallows in boiling water.
Add cold liquid.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat in mayonnaise. Stir in Cool Whip until blended.
Add cabbage and pineapple.
Pour into casserole or mold and chill until firm.

title: banana sandwiches
directions: Spread bread with peanut butter and mayonnaise.
Put banana between the two slices of bread and add lettuce, if desired.

title: jiffy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine horseradish and dry mustard and mix well.
Then add preserves, apple jelly and pepper.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers and cream cheese.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Combine margarine, butter, cream cheese and sugar; beat well.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and mix well.

title: busy day stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a large Dutch oven or iron pot.
Salt lightly as soup is very salty.
Pepper to taste.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours until meat is fork-tender.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: meatless "veal" parmesan
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix oatmeal, salt, oregano and parsley.
Stir oatmeal mixture and onion into eggs.
Form into patties.
Fry in hot oil until patties are thoroughly cooked and both sides are browned.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towels.
Discard any oil remaining in pan.
Return patties to pan.
Add tomato sauce. Top patties with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook until sauce is heated and cheese starts to melt.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: martha's tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all together and spread on flour tortillas.
Roll up and leave in refrigerator for awhile, then slice.

title: stuffing for 12 pound turkey
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add Brazil nuts, onion, celery, salt and Tabasco sauce; cook until nuts are lightly browned.
Add to bread crumbs and parsley.
Add water or stock.
Toss lightly with fork.
Stuff cavity of a 12 pound turkey or two 6 pound turkeys. May be baked separately.
Cover with foil for soft dressing or uncover for drier dressing.
Bake in a moderate 350° to 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook and brown sausage.
Drain.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
In a baking dish, grease bottom of pan, putting crescent rolls to make crust.
Layer sausage, hash browns and cheese and then egg mixture.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: lou's chuck wagon casserole
directions: Lightly saute pepper and onion in shortening.
Push aside. Saute meat, then combine all.
Sprinkle uncooked noodles over top. Add tomatoes and mushrooms, including juice.
Bring liquid to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 45 minutes, stirring several times.
Sprinkle cheese over top and continue simmering 15 minutes longer.

title: crispy okra
directions: Mix well.
You are now ready for dipping food. Remember to salt okra before dipping. Also may be used for fish, oysters or vegetables. Deep fry.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cut off 1-inch of the bottom of the stems.
Peel, quarter and slice 1/4-inch thick the rest of the stems.
Cook in 1 cup water along with the chopped onion and bouillon cube for 6 to 8 minutes until tender.
Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in pot; add 4 tablespoons flour and simmer a minute or two.
Add 3 cups milk and cook a few minutes until hot.
Add the cooked broccoli stems and water to the milk plus the 1 1/2 cups of broccoli florets and cook 2 or 3 more minutes.
Add the 1 teaspoon salt (or more) and a dash or 2 of ground red pepper (optional).
Serve with seasoned croutons.
Serves 4.

title: low-fat fruit cobbler(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a baking dish with vegetable cooking spray.
Pour fruit filling into baking dish (cover bottom).

title: muffin meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in muffin tins, preferably with liners.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in a large bowl; stir well.
Pour half of mixture into a greased 10-inch skillet.
Top with cheese.
Add remaining mixture.
Bake at 450° about 30 minutes or until done.

title: twenty-four hour omelet
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Butter 1 side of bread and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Place bread evenly in well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle bread with cheese.
Layer sausage on top of cheese.

title: turkey stir-fry supper
directions: Cut turkey into 2 inch strips.
In a Dutch oven or wok, stir-fry turkey in batches in oil for 5-7 minutes or until juices run clear.
Set turkey aside.
Add rice, 3 1/2 C. broth, soy sauce, garlic, ginger and pepper to pan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Cut broccoli into 3 inch pieces.
Add broccoli, carrots and onions to rice mixture; simmer for 3-5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and remaining broth; add to pan.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Stir in turkey and bean sprouts; heat through.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions; cool.
Punch holes in brownies with fork; pour Kahlua over brownies and set aside.
Make jello chocolate mousse according to package directions.
Break Skor bars into small pieces in food processor or by tapping them with a hammer right in wrapper.
Crumble half of the soaked brownies and place in bottom of a glass trifle dish. Cover with half of the mousse, layer with half of the candy and then add half of the whipped topping.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: ground steak
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix in flour.
Add can of soup. Simmer a short while.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Put in baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes, or until hot through.

title: gougere(makes 24)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly butter muffin tins.
In saucepan, combine water, butter and seasonings.
Heat until butter is melted and water boils steadily.
Add flour all at once; cook, stirring, until mixture pulls away from sides of pan and forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating each in thoroughly.
Add cheese and blend.
Spoon into tins, filling each one half full.
Bake until puffed and golden brown, about 25 minutes.

title: venison flank steak
directions: Place flank steak in shallow pan.
Combine other ingredients and pour over steak.
Let stand at room temperature for 3 to 4 hours, turning steak several times.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes per side.
Cut diagonally across grain of meat.

title: potatoes and tomatoes
directions: Place oil and onions in a skillet and cook on low for 3 minutes.
Add potatoes and tomatoes.
Season with spices and cover.
Cook on medium-low for about 20 minutes.
Uncover and cook an additional 5 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4.

title: reese's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.

title: monterey jack and green chile rice
directions: Cook the rice according to the directions on the package. While the rice is cooking prepare a buttered 3-quart casserole dish and preheat the oven to 325°.
After cooking the rice, while the rice is still hot, fold in the salt, white pepper, and sour cream.
In the buttered casserole dish, place a layer of 1/2 of the rice, 1/2 of the cheese, and 1/2 of the green chilies. For the second layer, add the remaining rice, green chilies, and the cheese on top.
Cook uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes, or until bubbly around the edges.

title: spice bars
directions: Combine raisins and water. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Stir in shortening, sugar and egg. Sift dry ingredients. Gradually add liquid mixture to dry ingredients. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 11 x 13-inch pan. Frost when cool with confectioners sugar frosting.

title: poor man's pie
directions: In large skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Add salt and pepper, drained corn and ketchup.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.

title: aunt maxine's log cabin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookies for cut-outs
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla. Combine the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Chill batter at least 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°. Roll out, cut and decorate as desired.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad:  country club style
directions: *You may substitute 1 1/2 cups crushed potato chips for almonds.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Sprinkle salt in skillet. Add chops and brown over medium heat.
Sprinkle chili mix over chops.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, cook onions in margarine over low heat until tender.
Add milk and pepper.
When milk is hot, stir in cheese.
Continue stirring until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli. Makes four 3/4 cup servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg, lemon juice and well mashed bananas.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and soda. Add to mixture, the nuts.
Turn into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° until tests done.
Slice thin and spread with cream cheese for sandwiches.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Boil potatoes for mashing.
Mix hamburger with breadcrumbs, salt and pepper to taste, egg and 1/2 cup of cream soup.
Put in cake pan; bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Drain fat from burger mixture.
Spread mashed potatoes on top.
Pour 1/2 cup cream soup on potatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Serve with gravy on top.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook hamburger, breaking it up as it cooks.
Drain off fat. Add other ingredients. Cook slowly, uncovered, to desired wetness. Serve on hamburger buns.
One pound makes 6 to 8 sandwiches on hamburger buns.

title: u-name it dessert
directions: Melt butter; add milk and sugar. Add peaches and Bisquick. Fold gently and pour into 8 or 9-inch greased baking dish. Sprinkle top with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve warm. Good with ice cream. Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to sugar, oil, eggs, apples, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cho-nut dessert squares
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: jalapeno spread
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Put first 4 ingredients in a food processor and blend well.
Mix in mayonnaise.
Store in a covered crock in refrigerator and serve with any type of crackers. Makes about 2 cups.

title: shrimp soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, gradually blend milk and 1 cup water into soup.
Add frozen rice, peas and mushrooms, shrimp, parsley and curry.
Cover and simmer gently for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: noodle-hamburger casserole(man's casserole)
directions: Brown onion and beef together; drain.
Cook noodles; drain. Mix ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: creme drops
directions: Optional: Add pecans, coconut or walnuts.

title: hot tomato cocktail
directions: Mix together all ingredients in an 8-ounce mug. Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until steaming.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Spread crescent rolls in the bottom of a large cookie sheet. Bake according to the instructions on the package; cool.
Mix together mayonnaise, cream cheese, sour cream and Hidden Valley Ranch dip mix.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Top with cut up vegetables.
Refrigerate until served.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and add the sugar.
Beat until light.
Add egg yolks and almond extract. Blend well. Add sifted flour and chopped almonds.
Mix thoroughly.
Form dough into balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: smoked sausage and bean soup
directions: In 4-quart Dutch oven, cook the onion and garlic in margarine or butter until tender but not brown.
Add the water, potatoes, sausage, beans and bouillon.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered for 15 minutes.
Add the cabbage or coleslaw mix, tomato paste or catsup and vinegar.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes more.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour with about 2/3 of the sweetener; crumble margarine into flour mixture with fingers until mixture is size of peas. Stir in egg with fork until well blended.
Work dough with hands until a smooth ball; divide into 3 sections.

Wrap 1/3 dough in waxed paper; store in refrigerator until ready for top crust. Grease 1 10-inch spring-form pan lightly; press remaining 2/3 dough firmly and evenly over bottom and about 3/4 way up the sides of pan; set aside.
Mix lemon juice and water; add apples a few at a time to the lemon-water to moisten each slice thoroughly.
When apples are moistened, squeeze moisture out with hands and place apples in large bowl.
Add raisins, balance of sweetener and cinnamon.
Stir and mix.
Place in crust.
Roll refrigerated 1/3 dough on well-floured board to 1 inch larger than pan.
Fit dough over apples, pressing side and top together with wet fingers. Prick pastry with fork several times.
Bake 1 hour, until apples are tender, at 375°.
Yield 12 servings.
Carbohydrate .38 g, protein 3.1 g, fat 7 g, calories 216.
One serving = 1 bread exchange, 2 fat exchange, 1 fruit exchange.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Bake the orange cake as directed on box, adding the orange flavoring.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cool. Mix together the Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Split cake and spread filling between the layers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add potato chips, vanilla and egg yolks.
Sift flour and soda together; add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Roll in balls.
Press down with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat 350° oven.
Mix flour, baking powder and 2 tablespoons of cocoa powder.
Mix milk, vanilla and butter; add to dry ingredients.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix all together.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: In skillet, heat meat and onion in butter until onion is tender.
In a bowl, combine meat mixture, chili peppers and cumin; set aside.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Turn pumpkin into saucepan and cook over direct heat for 10 minutes, until somewhat dry and slightly caramelized, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend the sugar, salt and spices. Stir into hot pumpkin.
Beat eggs, add milk and water.
Beat into pumpkin mixture until smooth.
Pour into pastry pan.
Bake in a hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to slow (300°) and continue baking, about 45 minutes longer or until pie tests done. Cool before serving.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Pour dressing over vegetables.
Let marinate overnight.
Add cherry tomatoes before serving (optional).

title: lasagna
directions: Saute minced garlic in frying pan and cook with ground beef. Then add and simmer: cut-up tomatoes, tomato sauce, Lawry's spaghetti sauce mix and seasonings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Crush garlic to a paste with the salt and sugar.
Add lard, green pepper and onions; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, parsley, thyme and bay leaf; cook over low heat about 1 hour, or until thick.
Add shrimp; cover the pan and simmer 5 minutes, or until done.
Season to taste with the Worcestershire and cayenne. Serve over rice.
Makes 2 generous servings.

title: eddie's catfish recipe
directions: Drain fish.
Put ingredients in plastic bag.
Pat fish dry with paper towel and shake in bag.
Place on rack in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Combine remaining ingredients except crumbs. Alternate with layer of macaroni in greased 2 quart casserole. Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potato and roasted pepper bake
directions: Cook onion in butter in a large saucepan till tender but not brown.
Stir in flour, salt, and pepper.
Add milk all at once. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese and parsley till cheese is melted. Meanwhile, thinly slice potatoes (about 6 cups).
Place half of the potatoes in a 2-quart rectangular baking dish.
Cover with half of the sauce.
Add all of the roasted peppers.
Repeat layers of potatoes and sauce.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more or till potatoes are tender.
Garnish with rosemary or parsley sprigs, if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: venison meatball stroganoff
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients and form into balls.
Brown in hot fat.
Remove from skillet.
Put the onion in the skillet and saute. Add the mushrooms and enough flour to make a paste.
Stir, then add the bouillon, sour cream, catsup, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce and salt, pepper and oregano to taste.
Bring to a boil. Turn to simmer.
Add meatballs and simmer 1 hour.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Combine graham crackers, margarine and 1/4 cup sugar and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, 2 eggs and 1/4 cup sugar and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Beat for three minutes and stir in nuts.
Bake in greased pan about thirty minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken, soup, broth, vegetables and seasonings and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a baking dish.

title: funny face salad for children
directions: Drain peaches.
Lay on plate flat side down.
Put black olive circles for eyes, raisins for nose and kiwi circle for a surprised mouth.
Put shredded cheese on top for hair.
Any other fresh fruits and vegetables available can be used also.

title: mud pies(non-edible)
directions: Mix dirt and water and pour into an old pan.
Place rocks around, if desired.
Decorate with leaves and sticks and let dry in the sun.
Do not eat!
Lots of fun!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix wet and dry ingredients well and place in a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: texas style baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add package of onion soup mix and 1 cup water; stir.
Add sugar, ketchup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Add beans and tomatoes.
Simmer until through or use crock-pot and simmer all day for more flavor.

title: snickerdoodles(from great-great grandmother)
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients, then add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer.

title: frosted creams
directions: Cook raisins in water until raisins are done.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients.
Pour juice from raisins, if not 1 cup add enough water to fill cup.
Add soda to water and add.
Mix raisins.
Bake in shallow pan.
May be frosted with powdered sugar icing while warm.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple.
Add enough water to this liquid to make 1 cup.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Stir in drained blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into a 2-quart flat dish.
Cover; put in refrigerator until firm. Combine the cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla; mix well.
Spread over congealed salad.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: rich and charlie's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with oil and wine vinegar.

title: caramel squares
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler. Stir cake mix with 1/3 cup evaporated milk, margarine and nuts. Press 1/2 of cake mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 or 6 minutes.
Take out of oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Drizzle melted caramels on top and dot remaining dough on top of this (dough will be wet).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool on rack and then refrigerate about 30 minutes until caramel sets.
Cut into squares.

title: egg casserole
directions: Pour bread and cheese in a 9-inch pan or 2-quart casserole. Mix beaten eggs, salt and milk and pour over bread and cheese. Refrigerate overnight. Set out at room temperature at least 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Layer refried beans in bottom of casserole dish.
Brown ground beef, drain and add taco seasoning.
Layer over beans.
Layer drained chilies.
Spread over top the shredded cheeses.
Bake in 400°
oven only until cheese is bubbly.
Remove.
Add layer of sour cream.
Top off with sliced olives.
Serve immediately with tortilla chips.

title: johnnycake
directions: Mix salt and corn meal.
Gradually stir in scalded milk or boiling water.
Spread 1/4-inch deep in a buttered shallow pan. If desired, dot with butter, in small bits.
Bake at 350° until crisp.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: You will need a broiling pan.

title: double-crispy chicken
directions: Crush and measure corn flakes into shallow pan or dish; set aside.
In small bowl, beat egg and milk slightly.
Add flour, salt and pepper; mix until smooth.
Dip chicken in batter, then roll in corn flakes.
Place single layer in greased or foil lined baking pan.
Drizzle with melted margarine or butter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Do not cover or turn chicken over.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and simmer over low flame for 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook slowly for 5 minutes longer.

title: moussaka (american style)
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Peel and slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick. Layer potato slices, beef, sauce and onion until casserole dish is full.
Bake, uncovered, approximately 1 hour, until potatoes are tender.
You may add your own spices to this dish or substitute potatoes with eggplant.
Tastes even better the second day.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Mix together beans, corn, soup, sour cream, onion, celery and green pepper; pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour melted margarine over cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caponata
directions: Slice eggplant and squeeze dry with paper towels. Dice into 1-inch cubes. Brown in hot oil 10 minutes or until soft and brown, adding onions during last 3 minutes of browning. Add tomatoes and celery. Simmer for 15 minutes. Add vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, olives and capers. Simmer 20 minutes longer over low heat. Tastes best when served at room temperature on crackers or crusty Italian bread.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together with hands. Roll into balls and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs, then sour cream, mixed with soda.
Use 9 x 9-inch pan, greased and floured.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter and swirl with knife.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix well; spread in a greased pan.
Bake at 300° about 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: fake heath bars
directions: Put foil paper at bottom of cookie sheet.
Grease and layer with saltines.
Melt butter, add sugar and let boil until looks like candy.
Pour over saltines.
Bake 10 minutes at 300°.
Take out of oven and pour Nestle morsels over it; spread.
Place in refrigerator for about 1 hour.

title: crock-pot garlic brown sugar chicken
directions: Cut chicken pieces into chunks. Place in crock-pot. Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken. Cook on low 6 to 8 hours. Serve over rice or noodles. Cooking time 6 hours, but will keep nice and moist for up to 3 hours.

title: "inside-out" chocolate bundt cake
directions: Combine pudding mix, cake mix, chocolate chips, milk and eggs in a very large bowl.
Mix by hand until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Fold in pecans.
Bake in greased Bundt pan in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly pressed with finger.
Cool for 30 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan.

title: mom's pie crust
directions: Be sure to measure exactly ingredients.
Place flour and salt in bowl; add shortening.
Mix until crumbly.
Add 6 tablespoons cold water.
Knead until it forms a soft ball.
Roll out with rolling pin.
Place in pie pans and crinkle the edges with thumb. Makes enough for 2 average size pies.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into bite size balls, chill.

title: english trifle
directions: Prepare cake and pudding mixes following package directions. In a large glass bowl, layer all of the ingredients in alternating layers until the bowl is filled.
Add a dash of sherry if desired.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt milk, candy and marshmallows together.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust and chill.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve 2 envelopes unflavored gelatin in 4 tablespoons cold water; add to 1 cup boiling water 1 cup pineapple juice, 1 cup crushed pineapple, 1 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and juice of 1 lemon.
Mix all.
Add 1 envelope Dream Whip after partially jelled; jell until firm.
Break up angel food cake into pieces.
Line large bowl with waxed paper.
Start with cake on bottom, then cream mixture on next row, then cake, then cream mixture and continue alternating.
Chill overnight.
Frost with Dream Whip.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat
egg
yolks, sugar and juice together.
Sift flour and baking powder several times.
Add eggs and sugar.
Fold in egg whites, well beaten.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: carrie's quiche
directions: Defrost spinach and drain (do not cook).
Mix eggs, cream and milk; add salt, pepper, lemon juice and parsley.
Stir in spinach and Feta cheese.
Fill quiche crust; place Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out dry.
Serve with a salad.

title: mama terry's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix in buttermilk, eggs, melted butter and vanilla.

title: bacon-cheese-mushroom burgers
directions: Combine cheese, mushrooms, bacon and mayonnaise; refrigerate. Grill burgers over medium-hot coals for 10 to 12 minutes, turning once.
During the last 3 minutes, spoon 1/4 cup of the cheese mixture onto each burger.
Serve on buns.

title: peas and mushrooms
directions: Melt butter.
Add celery and onion and cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients and cook until thoroughly heated.
This recipe can be easily done in the microwave.

title: baby back ribs
directions: Mix spices together. Rub into ribs.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 225°.
Very good in slow cooker.

title: the baldpate inn corn bread
directions: Heat oven to
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Using an electric mixer, beat butter and sugar until blended and smooth. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Gradually beat in corn and cheeses. Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening until creamy.
Add eggs, then add water and vanilla.
Sift flour, spices and salt together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add apples and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix all ingredients well with hands.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press with tines of a fork in crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool.
Serve at room temperature. Makes 8 dozen, 40 calories each.
These freeze very well.

title: mushroom rice
directions: First, melt butter in baking pan.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Next, pour in baking pan with butter.
Bake at 350° for an hour and a half.

title: spinach salad
directions: Rinse and drain spinach.
Tear and place into a salad bowl. In small saucepan, combine lemon juice, honey, garlic and pepper; bring to a boil.
Fry bacon.
Crumble bacon and egg on top of spinach.
Pour honey mixture over salad.
Serve immediately.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Heat oil in a large pot.
Add next 8 ingredients and saute, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except milk and parsley.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in milk.
Heat but do not boil.
Garnish with parsley.

title: monkey bread
directions: Generously grease Bundt pan with butter.
In plastic bag, mix sugars and cinnamon.
Shake a few biscuit pieces at a time in plastic bag and place in Bundt pan.
Spread remaining mixture on top.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan while still hot (approximately 10 minutes) upside down.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Add flour and milk alternately, starting and ending with flour.
Add flavorings and beat well.
Bake in a tube or Bundt pan, greased and floured, at 350° for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to 325° and continue baking 1/2 hour.

title: apple butter
directions: Boil cider or juice until reduced by 1/2.
Add apples.
Cook 1/2 hour or until tender.
Put apples through food press and return to pan.
Cook again until thickened.
Add sugar and spices (if desired) to taste and cook until sugar is dissolved.
Follow canning instructions from your canner to process.

title: master mix
directions: Using a very large mixing bowl sift together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, cream of tartar and dry milk; sift again. With pastry blender, cut in oil until mixture is consistency of cornmeal.
Store in tightly covered container at room temperature. Mix will keep for 6 weeks.
To measure pile mix lightly into cup and level with spatula.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Stir together first three ingredients and roll into balls. Melt chips and paraffin together in the top of a double boiler. Roll peanut butter balls in mixture and set on wax paper.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften, then mix with dried beef.
Stir and mix thoroughly all ingredients and serve hot with crackers.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix water, salt, sugar	and
yeast and set aside for 10 minutes.
Add both flours
and oil to mixture and stir together. Let rise about 1
hour.
Stir
and	let rise again.
Stir once more.
Divide dough
into
half.
Place
in
greased loaf pans. Let rise until top of
pan.
Bake
at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: meat loaf surprise
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Roll or pat out flat on waxed paper to edge.
Sprinkle with cheese and mushrooms.
Roll up, sealing ends.
Put in loaf pans.
(Makes two loaves.)
Bake at 350°, covered with foil, for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover for last 15 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Place chuck roast in slow cooker. Combine remaining ingredients in mixing bowl. Pour barbecue sauce mixture over chuck roast. Cover and cook on low eight to ten hours or on high for four or five hours. Remove chuck roast from slow cooker and shred meat. Place shredded meat back in slow cooker. Stir meat to evenly coat with sauce. Spoon meat into sandwich buns and top with additional barbecue sauce if desired.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Pat into 9 x 12-inch pan the crumbs and melted oleo.
Beat for 10 minutes the oleo, eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over crust. Cut bananas lengthwise and put on mixture.
Drain large can of pineapple and pour over.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Decorate with cherries cut in half and crushed nuts.

title: circus peanut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cut up candies and dissolve in hot water.
Drain pineapple and add the liquid to the cold water. Add to first mixture; allow to set partially.
Then add whipped Dream Whip and the crushed pineapple.
Let set.
(You may also use whipped cream or Cool Whip.)

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper in skillet.
Drain off fat. Stir in next 6 ingredients (let simmer).
Cook noodles.
In separate bowl, mix the cream cheese, sour cream, cottage cheese and green onion.
Use 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer half of noodles (on bottom), half of ground beef mixture and all of cream cheese mixture.
Put on rest of noodles, and rest of ground beef (in order listed).
Put shredded Monterey Jack cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes (if cold, bake for 45 minutes).
Bake 20 minutes covered with aluminum foil and 10 minutes uncovered.

title: sausage roll
directions: Roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cook sausage.
When completely cooked, add eggs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Spread on dough. Then roll up dough as a jelly roll.
Place in a warm place and let rise 1/2 hour.
Cook in a 375° oven until crust is golden, about 35 minutes.

title: ham rollups
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Spread cheese on ham slices; roll up from long side.
Slice into 1/2 inch thick rounds. Place on serving plate.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika and garnish with parsley.

title: andy boy broccoli chicken bake
directions: Barely cook broccoli spears.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Arrange the chicken on top.
Cover with soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder, all mixed together.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Top with soft bread crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Make layers of peas, soup, eggs, cheese, pepper and cracker crumbs until all are used.
Make a sauce of milk, flour and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: poor man's soup
directions: Cut
Cheddar
cheese
into cubes; set aside.
Cook spaghetti in	1-quart
of water.
Do not drain!
Add tomatoes and cheese. Simmer
on low heat for 15 minutes.
Serve while hot. Serves 6.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Bone chicken breasts and remove skin.
Slice horizontally into slices (1/8 inch thick); then cut into squares.
Arrange on tray. Slice mushrooms.
Cut green parts off onions into 1-inch long pieces; slice white part 1/4 inch thick.
Arrange on tray.
Pour chicken broth into small pitcher.
Mix soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Pour into pitcher.
Place oil and nuts in container. Arrange ingredients at table with electric frypan.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil to 350°.
Add cashews, all at once.
Cook 1 minute, shaking pan.
Remove and set aside.
Add remaining oil and chicken. Cook quickly, turning until opaque.
Add mushrooms and broth. Cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Stir in soy sauce and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Simmer 1 minute, uncovered.
Mix in onions.
Sprinkle with cashews.
Serve over bed of white rice.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine vegetables with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Place remaining ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Cool and drain vegetables; add vinegar mixture.
Stir gently.
Put into plastic freezer container and freeze.
When ready to use, defrost and serve chilled.
Yields 1 1/2 to 2 quarts.

title: corn relish
directions: Put all ingredients in pot. Cook until tender. Place in pint jars and seal.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Combine the flour, shortening, baking powder and salt until crumbly.
Add the water slowly.
Knead 3 minutes.
Cover and let rest 15 minutes or until slightly bloated and shiny.
Form into 1 1/2 -inch balls.
Roll thin and cook on ungreased griddle.

title: angel sweets
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate pieces and butter over low heat. Remove from heat; blend in egg.
Stir in sugar, nuts and marshmallows, blending well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill.
Makes about 48 pieces.

title: hamburger macaroni soup
directions: Crumble hamburger into 3-quart microwave dish.
Add carrot, onion and garlic.
Cook 4 minutes and stir.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes longer and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except 1 cup water.
Cover and cook.
Stir every 6 minutes until vegetables and macaroni are tender.

title: strawberry daiquiris
directions: Mix ingredients in a Tupperware container that can be put in the freezer.
Beat ingredients with mixer.
Freeze for 3 days.

title: western meal in one
directions: Brown beef with garlic and onion; drain.
In 2-quart casserole dish, combine the meat.
Mix salt, chili powder, beans, tomatoes, rice and meat.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese and olives.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: san francisco salad
directions: Heat soup and milk to boiling; stir in vegetables.
Cover; cook over low heat for 20 minutes, or until veggies are tender. Stir in cheese and heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chuck wagon mac
directions: Prepare dinner as directed.
Brown hamburger.
Add celery, green pepper and onion, cook until tender.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Add dinner, mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Using
your prettiest chafing dish, melt the jelly over medium heat.
Add
the
drained cherries and heat thoroughly. When the cherries
are
hot, float the brandy on top of them. Don't stir. Give
the
liqueur a moment to heat through, then set afire.
Just before the flames die, ladle the cherries and juice over rich vanilla ice cream and serve immediately.

title: ocean catfish cajun style
directions: Heat butter in a skillet to 250°.
Saute onions, green pepper and garlic for 2 minutes.
Add fish and saute 3 minutes on each side.
Season with Cajun seasoning.
Cover fish mixture with tomato sauce.
Cover skillet and simmer 6 to 8 minutes.
Serve with rice, salad and French bread.

title: old settler beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown hamburger, bacon and onion in skillet. In large pot, add all the beans with juice (do not drain beans). Add meat mixture to beans. In bowl, mix together next 6 ingredients; add to meat and bean mixture.
Bake 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, eggs and flavoring well.
Add dry ingredients; refrigerate 2 hours.
May be rolled out and cut into shapes or dropped by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate cream roll sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook over low heat until thickened.
Cool before serving on roll.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pumpkin crunch cream pie
directions: Pour milk into mixing bowl.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, one minute.
Let stand 5 minutes. Blend in pumpkin, spice, almonds, chips and 2 cups of Cool Whip. Spoon into pie crust.
Chill 4 hours.
Just before serving, garnish with remaining Cool Whip and chocolate curls.

title: pasta and bean soup(inexpensive and nutritious)
directions: Bring water to rapid boil. Add garlic, salt, pepper, chickpeas (with juice) and oil.
Bring
to rolling boil.
Add pasta (and onion and bouillon, if desired). Cook until pasta is tender. Do not drain.
Serve with grated Parmesan or Romano cheese and a loaf of crisp bread.
This soup may be reheated in microwave.

title: cornbread topped bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain.
Stir in drained chilies, beans, seasoning mix and water.
Spread into 8-inch glass baking dish.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: party pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in single layer in baking pan.
Place 1 onion slice topped with 1 lemon slice on center of each chop.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg, salt and cinnamon.
Make two crusts. Put lower crust in pan.
Put half of mixture in crust.
Fill in apples.
Put balance of mixture.
Dot with oleo.
Put on top crust.
Brush with milk.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 40 minutes at 350°.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash and dry
lettuce.
Crisp-fry bacon; drain on paper towel and crumble.
Combine vinegar, water and sugar.
Heat to boiling point.
Tear lettuce into pieces in large bowl; add bacon and pour dressing over all.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves four.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add strawberries and eggs, along with oil.
By hand, mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh marinated vegetables
directions: You will need 4 c. fresh vegetables cut into bite-sized pieces. Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup parsley in a large heavy pot.
Add enough water to cover vegetables.
Cover tightly and cook over medium heat until vegetables are just tender but still crisp. This will take 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from heat, remove cover and let vegetables cool in the pot.
When cool, transfer to serving dish.
Cover; chill to allow flavors to blend.
Bring to room temperature to serve.
Top with remaining parsley.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 16 g, protein 4 g, fat 24 g, calories 297.

title: hungry hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain fat.
Add green beans, drained, and the can of soup.
Pour into a casserole.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat sugar and margarine just until blended.

Increase speed to high; beat until light and fluffy. Reduce speed to low; add sour cream, orange juice, vanilla, orange, lemon and rum flavorings; add eggs and beat until blended. Add flour, salt and baking soda; beat until well mixed.
Spoon batter into prepared tube pan and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool pan on wire rack.
Sprinkle cake with confectioners sugar.

title: blueberry trifle
directions: Prepare filling. Cream together both packages cream cheese and condensed milk.

title: cabbage supreme(rose's original)
directions: *Vegetable oil and bacon bits can be used instead of bacon drippings.

title: amaretto truffles
directions: Melt all together, then add flavorings.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in ground nutmeal, coconut, powdered cocoa, powdered sugar, etc.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place margarine in bowl and melt. Melt margarine in 2-quart baking dish. Combine flour, sugar, milk and 1/4 cup syrup from peaches. Pour into baking dish. Top with canned peaches. Do not mix. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Line 12 muffin tins with muffin cups.
Place 1 vanilla wafer (flat side down) in each muffin cup.

title: hungry man's dish
directions: Brown beef and pour off fat.
Add sugar, salt and tomato sauce.
Cook and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain water.
Blend onions with sour cream and cream cheese.

title: yum - a - setta
directions: Brown burger with salt, pepper, brown sugar and onion.
Add tomato soup and set aside.
Cook noodles and drain.
Stir in chicken soup, adding a dash of milk to help mix.
Layer 1/2
each burger mix, noodle mix and cheese. Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Use well-greased casserole.
Put shrimp, bread and cheese in layers in casserole.
Pour melted butter over ingredients.
Beat eggs and milk with seasonings and pour over other ingredients. Let stand overnight in refrigerator in a covered casserole. Sprinkle potato chips on top and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: gooey shoo-fly pie
directions: Beat eggs and molasses.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add to egg mixture.
Mix crumb ingredients well with hands and reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Mix remaining crumbs with goo.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then 325° for 35 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add drained whole kernel corn, creamed corn, bell pepper, pimentos, rice, sugar and egg.
Season to taste.
Pour into greased, shallow pan and cover with grated cheese.
Bake until bubbly at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients together (reserving 1/2 cup chocolate chips) until smooth.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle top with reserved chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain pears (save 1 cup liquid).
Boil liquid; add jello. Stir until dissolved.
Let partially set.
Blend cream cheese and pears in blender or with a potato masher.
Add jello mixture and pecans.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Place in mold or pan.

title: beef barbecue (sloppy joes)
directions: Fry hamburger and onions until meat is brown.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer.
This recipe will yield 20 barbecues.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients until smooth.
Line an 11 x 14-inch jelly roll pan with wax paper and grease sides of pan. Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove immediately and place on linen towel that has been sprinkled with confectioners sugar; remove wax paper and roll cake in towel. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: red, white and green salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir well.
Add mayonnaise mixture to the next four vegetables.
Chill overnight.
Line serving bowl with lettuce leaves and fill with salad before serving.

title: lipton's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, lightly mix together meat with soup mix, eggs, catsup, bread crumbs and water.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in shallow baking pan and gently pack.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tuna or chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles until almost done and drain.
In a large bowl, mix all your cans of soup as directed.
Add the sour cream, salt and pepper and mix good.
Add the mixed vegetables and tuna and mix again.
In a large roasting pan, pour your noodles and spread good to cover bottom of pan.
Pour soup and vegetable mixture over the noodles and bake about 30 minutes in a 400° oven.
Take out and sprinkle crushed Ritz cracker crumbs over the top.
Return to oven about 5 minutes.
Serve with salad crackers for complete meal.

title: caramel pie
directions: Cook in a saucepan on low heat the butter, eggs, vanilla, flour and milk until it starts to thicken.
Brown sugar in iron skillet; pour into milk mixture.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Be sure to separate eggs if you like a meringue top.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, egg and onion, stirring well.
Carefully drop batter by tablespoons into deep hot oil (370°).
Cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Fry until hush puppies are golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain well on absorbent towels.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter until combined. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; combine with cream cheese mixture.
Add milk and stir until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into 2 pie crusts.
Freeze until shortly before serving time.

title: peking bean sprouts
directions: Heat the oil in a skillet; saute the bean sprouts for 1 minute, stirring steadily.
Mix in the ginger and salt.
Cover and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in the green onions and soy sauce; cook 3 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: meat loaf surprise
directions: Microwave vegetables according to package instructions.
Mix together meat, egg and bread crumbs.
Place meat mixture between 2 sheets of Saran Wrap and flatten with rolling pin.
Remove top sheet after flattening.
Sprinkle on cheese, then mushrooms and vegetables.
Roll the meat into a jelly roll shape, using bottom sheet of Saran Wrap to help.
Lift onto a cookie sheet, seam side down.
Discard second sheet of Saran Wrap.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until done.

title: good neighbor recipe
directions: Blend together all ingredients. Serve generous portions to everyone you meet.

title: easy schnitzel
directions: Cut meat into 6 serving size pieces; pound to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut small slits in fat edges to prevent curling. Combine eggs and the water.
Stir together dry potatoes, cheese and salt.
Dip each piece of veal in egg mixture, then in potato mixture; repeat dipping to give each a second coating.
In skillet, brown veal in hot Crisco for 3 minutes.
Turn carefully and brown second side about 3 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Bake shell.
Remove from oven and cool.
In a medium bowl, beat the egg yolks until thick.
Blend in the condensed milk using a whisk for this and the following step.
Gradually add the lime juice.
Spoon the mixture into the cooled shell.
Preheat the oven to 350°.

title: swiss green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions. Drain well and place in casserole dish.
Combine butter, salt, pepper, onion, sugar and sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour over beans. Top with Swiss cheese and cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef king ranch casserole
directions: Add oil to large heated skillet and saute onions, peppers and jalapeno.
Mix in all spices and cook until onion is translucent. Add milk, Ro-Tel and broth; bring to a simmer.
Remove from heat; stir in beef and cheese.
Cut tortillas into quarters and place half into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with half of the beef mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: rice pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine rice, salt, egg and 1 cup cheese.
Press over bottom of 12-inch pizza pan, making outer edge slightly higher.
Top with pizza sauce and favorite pizza ingredients.
Bake 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine
and
sugar.
Add
eggs, one at a time. Add lemon extract, 2 cups flour with baking powder sifted into it. Cut
fruit
and
dredge
with the remaining 2 cups flour. Add dredged
fruit
and
nuts to batter.
Turn into a prepared tube pan (line with wax paper) and bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Put a pan of water under the cake while baking.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Add rice to rapidly boiling water; add salt and butter.
Cook and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add milk and vanilla.
Simmer 15 minutes longer.
Thoroughly blend eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add a small amount of the hot mixture to egg mixture blend.
Add to hot mix; cook 5 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Pour into heated serving dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve while still warm.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together. Add flour and baking powder, beating well. Bring milk and butter to a boil. Beat in preceding mixture and add vanilla. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a tube pan.

title: potato-hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Add 1/3 can water to vegetable soup and add to hamburger.
Fix potatoes and hamburger-soup mixture in layers and repeat until all is used. Add 1/3 can water to mushroom soup and pour over top of casserole.
Bake 1 hour.

title: ribbon jello
directions: Pour strawberry jello, hot water and ice cream in 11 x 13-inch glass pan.
Make a lemon jello with 1 cup hot water and 1/2 pint of ice cream.
Same as last with orange jello.
With lime jello, make as other.
Pour each jello as first.
Makes ribbon jello.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Add water to a large boiling pot.
Chop potatoes and onions. Put baby carrots in whole.
Mix all vegetables with water.
Stir in tomato paste.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook at medium heat for two hours.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix with mixer. Add a little water at a time to make a smooth-like dough.
Roll into balls.
Make little patties or mold. Dip into chocolate.

title: burger bundles
directions: Make stuffing according to directions; cool.
Mix meat and milk together.
Pat into 12 (6-inch) circles.
Spoon 1/4 cup stuffing on each circle.
Draw edges up and seal into a ball. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat soups, sauce and catsup until bubbly.
Pour over bundles.
Very good.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: drop date cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, salt and soda water.
Set aside.
In saucepan, cook dates, sugar and water until mixture is paste-like.
Drop dough onto greased cookie sheet.
Indent center with spoon and fill with date paste.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: oven pan cake
directions: Stir batter, pour over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Blend in egg.
Spread onto bottom of pastry shell uneven.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Saute chopped onions in butter with garlic until yellow.
Add salt, curry powder and shrimp.
Heat until shrimp are completely done.
Add soup and raisins.
Add sour cream 15 minutes before serving.
Serve Shrimp Curry over rice.
Have sauce and rice very hot.

title: peach pudding
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Cream flour, sugar, baking soda, milk and vanilla together and pour into melted butter.
Pour peaches on top and bake at 375° until cake is done.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, green pepper, 1/2 cup salsa and cream cheese in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture onto each tortilla; roll up.
Place seam side down in lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Stir cheese spread and milk in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Pour sauce over tortillas; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Pour remaining salsa over tortillas.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: canned cucumber relish
directions: Slice unpeeled cucumbers and dice other vegetables.
Place in large canning pot and cover with salt and water.
Soak 12 hours. When time has passed, heat vinegar, sugar and spices.
Drain water off vegetables and add hot vinegar mixture.
Bring to a boil, approximately 10 minutes or until mixture is well heated. Transfer to hot canning jars and seal with hot disks and rings.

title: christmas trees
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in a large pan. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and food coloring. Fold in Cheerios. Cool. Butter hands and shape 2/3 cup mixture into tree on wax paper. Add gumdrop slices and a star on a toothpick.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop cooked broccoli and add the eggs, soup, onions, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into a well buttered baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Then top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter or margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for about 25 or 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 3 separate pans.
In a glass bowl, put layer of cake, then layer of crushed pineapple, then layer of strawberries, then layer of Cool Whip. Repeat until 3 layers thick.
Top with some whole strawberries.
Moist and makes pretty dish.

title: chalumpas
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot (slow cooker).
Cover with water.
Cook over low heat for 12 hours.
Take bones out and break up roast meat.
Cook another 12 hours.
Serve over Fritos with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, olives, sour cream and salsa.

title: squirrel and squirrel gravy
directions: Skin, clean and cut up the 2 squirrels.
Put them in a pot and pour in enough water to completely cover them.
Cook until tender. Take the squirrels out and save the broth to make the gravy.
Roll the squirrels in flour and fry in a skillet in Crisco until brown like chicken.
Take the broth you saved and get it ready to boil; pour in a mixture of 3/4 cup of milk and 2 tablespoons of flour. Stir until it thickens.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except coconut) and shape into small balls.
Roll in coconut.
Keep in refrigerator or freezer.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding and pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: easy sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare tube pan.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add 1 cup sugar; blend.
Add 1/2 cup flour; blend.
Add 1/2 cup flour and baking powder mixture; blend. Add water gradually.
Blend.
Add flavoring.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: shrimp toast
directions: Mix all together using a hand mixer, then spread on English muffins.
Place muffins on cookie sheet and put in a 350° oven until toasted.
Cut muffin slices into 4, then serve.

title: no bake peanut butter pie
directions: In a medium bowl, combine powdered sugar and cream cheese until mixed well.
In a separate bowl, mix together warm water and gelatin and then add mixture to cream cheese mixture.
Quickly add peanut butter and Cool Whip to the mixture.
Pour into the graham cracker crust.
Chill for 1 hour.
Will keep in the refrigerator for 2-3 days.

title: christmas pudding(my grandmother's recipe)
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add lemon rind and nutmeg.
Add beaten eggs gradually.
Sift flour, spice, soda and salt together and add fruit also.
Add crumbs and brandy and mix well.
Tie securely in well floured pudding cloth, allowing room to swell. (May use calico or muslin.)
Keep boiling in large saucepan (adding boiling water as needed) for 6 to 8 hours and hang to dry. Alternately it may be cooked in a steamer.
Reheat when ready to serve by boiling for 1 hour.
Serve with custard and/or brandy butter.

title: noodle candy
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler.
Stir in noodles and nuts with rubber spatula.
Spoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Place in tightly covered container.

title: cheesy luncheon bake
directions: Heat vegetable mixture as directed on package.
Add tuna and stir lightly.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 45 to 60 seconds or until heated through.
Makes about 1 serving, 240 calories.

title: grilled vegetable kabobs
directions: Place potatoes in medium saucepan.
Add water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 12 minutes.
Drain well.
Cut each potato in half.
Clean the mushrooms with damp paper towels.
Remove stems, reserving stems for another use. Thread potatoes, mushrooms, tomatoes and peppers alternately onto six 12-inch wooden skewers.
Place kabobs in a large, shallow dish.
Combine Italian dressing and next 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Brush over kabobs.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 4 hours. Coat grill rack with cooking spray.
Place on grill over medium-hot coals.
Place kabobs on rack and cook 12 to 13
minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into a greased skillet and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add cheese the last 30 minutes of baking.

title: grape-nut salad
directions: Mix pudding as instructed on box.
Add the Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Not too long before serving, add the bananas and Grape-Nuts.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Base:
Mix jello with boiling water, Seven-Up, crushed pineapple and bananas.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch container.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Cream oleo well.
Add sugar.
Cream until fluffy.
Mix vanilla and water in.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Add nuts and mix.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Shape into date size.
Bake and immediately after baking roll in dish with extra powdered sugar.
Be gentle.
Bake at 325° for 23 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in order given and pour into a 10-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook 45 minutes more.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour.
Stir in milk and soup.
Cook slowly until sauce thickens.
Add seafood.
Stir in sherry.
Serve on toast points.

title: stewed rhubarb
directions: Boil together the first 3 ingredients for 3 minutes; pour over the rhubarb in baking dish. Cover; bake for 20 minutes,
or until bubbly, at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mash cooked potatoes.
All all ingredients together and put into baking dish.

title: parsley dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Very good for raw vegetables.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Mix peas, onion, bell pepper and celery and let marinate in refrigerator overnight.
About 2 to 3 hours before serving, add the egg, mayonnaise, sugar and mustard.
Sugar may be reduced or omitted for diet reasons.

title: red raspberry rose punch
directions: In large punch bowl, add all but strawberries; stir, then add strawberries.
Serve immediately.

title: spoon rolls(makes about 18 rolls)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and stir.
Add sugar, oil, egg and flour.
Mix with spoon and drop into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for about 18 to 20 minutes.
(The rolls may be refrigerated and used later or frozen.)

title: italian sausage and peppers
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, heat Italian sausage links with water to boiling.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Remove cover; continue cooking and turning sausages frequently until water evaporates and sausage links are well browned, about 20 minutes. Remove sausages to paper towels to drain.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, oil, garlic salt, onion, parsley and seasonings.
Blend in grated cheese and Bisquick.
Fold in zucchini.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in small squares.

title: chicken empandas
directions: Combine chicken, chilies, cottage cheese and Monterey Jack cheese in medium bowl; stir well.
Set aside.
Combine 3/4 cup flour, 1/4 cup corn meal and red pepper in a large bowl.
Cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture is like coarse corn meal.
Sprinkle cold water, 1 tablespoon at a time, evenly over surface of mixture.
Stir with fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Shape into a ball.
Cover and chill 10 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Pour everything into greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for at least 1 hour.
Stir once during baking.

title: quick pigs in a blanket
directions: Chop cabbage in medium pieces.
Spread in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Brown meat and onion in large skillet, break up meat with spoon as it cooks.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper. Spoon mixture over cabbage.
In small saucepan, heat tomato soup and water to boiling.
Pour over all ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Fluff lightly with fork.
Serves 4.

title: apricot-orange jello mold
directions: Combine ingredients by bringing to a boil.
Pour into bowl and refrigerate. When completely cooled, decorate with Cool Whip.

title: fruit punch
directions: Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: blackberry muffins
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
In separate bowl beat eggs. Add blackberries and oil.
Blend dry ingredients into liquids. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in muffin tins.

title: danish coffee barsfort collins, colorado
directions: Mix like pie dough, when half forms, put on cookie sheet and roll wit hands to cover cookie sheet.

title: chafing dish meat balls(serves 16 to 20)
directions: Combine beef, egg, onion and salt.
Shape into small balls. Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice.
Drop in meat balls and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve warm in chafing dish with sauce.

title: dream whip pecan pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, nuts and margarine.
Gradually beat sugar and vanilla into egg whites.
Fold crumb mixture into egg mixture.
Pour into a well-greased pie pan and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped topping.

title: potato bake
directions: Put hash browns in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese.
Pour whipping cream over it.
Cover with melted butter.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mom's dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; pack cucumbers, dill and small pieces of garlic into a 2-quart canning jar.
Mix syrup together and pour cold over filled jars.
Place jars in a canner of cold water that comes to the neck of the jars.
Make sure rack is in canner.
Put on burner and let come to a boil and boil until pickles change to a lighter green color.
Take out of canner; tighten to seal. Pickles are ready to eat in a week.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat egg. Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 375°.

title: "indiana" chili(country:  u. s. a.)
directions: Brown ground chuck in a skillet.
Use a fork to break the meat into small pieces.
Cook until meat is done; drain excess fat. Sprinkle salt and chili powder over meat; mix well.
Then add onion.
Cook until onion is tender.

title: wine drop cookies(old recipe)
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and molasses and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, alternately with liquid. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven until done, about 10 minutes.

title: metza pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; press into a pie pan.
Top with Parmesan cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: canning apple pie filling
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and water and add the apples in large pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until apples are tender.
Pack into sterilized jars; seal with lids that are in boiling water.
Tighten lids and invert until sealed, overnight to be safe.

title: stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Scoop out pulp from potato halves into mixing bowl, leaving 1/4 in. shells.
Mash pulp; reserve shells.
Add remaining ingredients to potato pulp; mix well.
