Spoon potato mixture evenly into reserved shells; place on baking sheet and bake until heated through, about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: quick cobblers
directions: Spray 9 x 9-inch pan with vegetable spray.
Put can of pie filling in pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top, using whole box. Put pats of butter on top of dry mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Creates its own crust!
This is great served warm with ice cream.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Let cool.
Poke holes in top and pour Kahlua over cake.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Prepare mousse. Crush Heath bars.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine and combine with all other ingredients except the chocolate and paraffin.

title: banana pudding
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, add 3 cups milk and margarine.
Mix sugar and flour and salt.
Set aside.
In remaining cup of milk, add egg yolks.
Mix and add to milk and margarine.
After margarine has melted, add flour, sugar and salt.
Bring to boil on medium heat. When at a full rolling boil, add vanilla and turn off.
Arrange wafers on bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass dish with bananas.
Add pudding after cooled.
Arrange more wafers on top.

title: sharon's taco salad
directions: Brown meat with onion and green pepper.
Drain and blot.
Mix the next 5 ingredients with the meat mixture.
Serve hot or cold. This looks nice on a bed of lettuce.
On the side have the remaining ingredients.
This way the vegetables don't get soggy. Leftovers can be used the next day.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well in casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla, stirring well. Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes more.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly buttered cookie sheet. Spread thin; let cool.
Break into small pieces.

title: lemon broiled fish
directions: Combine lemon juice, sherry, lemon peel, salt, paprika and thyme leaves in a small bowl.
Place fillets on broiler pan.
Spray fish directly with Pam for about 2 1/2 seconds.
Pour lemon juice mixture evenly over fish.
Broil until done, about 5 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy italian chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Oven brown biscuits in casserole for 10 minutes (5 minutes for boneless, skinless breasts).
Remove from oven; season with salt and pepper.
Baste with Italian dressing. Lower oven temperature to 350° and bake, uncovered, for 50 minutes (30 to 35 minutes for boneless, skinless breasts), basting every 10 minutes.
Do not turn breasts.

title: cherry cake
directions: Blend sugar and eggs. Add flour, nuts and flavoring.
Bake in long pan in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream cake number 2
directions: Crush enough Oreo cookies to cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine Oreos and melted margarine and press into pan.
Open ice cream carton completely so that ice cream can be sliced.
Slice ice cream and place over cookies.
Pour chocolate syrup over ice cream and freeze about an hour.
Spread Cool Whip over top and garnish with cookie crumbs if desired.
Freeze 2 to 3 hours or overnight before serving to allow cake to freeze firmly.

title: stuffed polish sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and sausage.
Stuff mixture into halved Polish sausage; top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cook pineapple juice, egg, sugar, flour and vinegar until thick; cool.
Dice apples (leave peeling on).
Mix together all ingredients.
Sprinkle more peanuts over top.
Refrigerate.

title: roast wild canadian goose stuffed with a moist apple stuffing
directions: Canadian geese are reaching all time high population levels and this tremendous natural resource makes a fine addition to the dinner table.
The goose should be harvested, cleaned and prepared as one would any fine fowl.
Prior to preparing the goose, rinse and coat lightly with salt and pepper.
Return the goose to the refrigerator while the stuffing is prepared.
The stuffing is to keep the goose moist and add flavor while cooking; it is not to be eaten.

title: holiday mold
directions: Mix packages of lemon and lime jello with hot water and let cool.
Add pineapple and juice.
Add sour cream.
Set in a ring mold.

title: hunt's tomato spice cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the first 8 ingredients.
Add tomato sauce, baking soda, eggs, oil, nuts, raisins and fruit juice.
Mix well, then pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before turning out on serving plate.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Make into round balls and place in baking dish. (Also, add 1/4 cup minced onion and some garlic.)

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix pineapple with juice and pudding mix. Add yogurt, blending well. Put in pie crust and chill.

title: lobster dien bien
directions: Cut lobster in small pieces.
Season with 1/2 teaspoon pepper and 1/3 teaspoon salt.
Brown in 4 ounces of butter in pan. Partly brown lobster in butter.
Chop scallions, green pepper and mushrooms and add to lobster.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add rice, stirring continuously until rice is loose.
Add tomatoes and consomme.
Stir and cover.
Cook about 25 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Brown remaining 2 ounces butter; add tarragon and pepper. Pour over lobster and mix well.
Serves 3.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Put in crock-pot.
Cook on medium for 3 hours.

title: oven baked beans
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and bake in casserole dish in slow oven 2 to 3 hours until thick.

title: spicy turkey chili
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes. Remove from heat and serve hot with shredded cheese.

title: congealed shrimp salad
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Boil tomato sauce and mix well with gelatin and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.
May be set in mold for serving at weddings or showers. Serve with crackers.

title: mexican tortilla dip
directions: Put cream cheese in a 9-inch pie plate and press against the sides and bottom.
Mix chili beans and other ingredients
and put in pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Pour over jello, softened cream cheese and marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add pecans, coconut and fruit cocktail.
Mix well.
Spray mold or dish with pam.
Pour gelatin mixture into mold.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken tetrazzini(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan; add flour.
Stir until smooth paste.
Add milk and stir continually and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Sauce should have the consistency of thick cream. Add salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Stir.
Remove from stove and stir in cheese and egg yolk rapidly.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: potato crown casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Add tomato, broccoli, mushrooms, soup and half the cheese.
In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, layer potato crowns on the bottom and the sides.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. When potato crowns are solid, add mixture and bake for 30 minutes. In the last few minutes, add remaining cheese.

title: potato pie(pytpalek)
directions: Boil potatoes with skins
in salted water until tender. Cool potatoes and remove skins.	It's
best to cook potatoes a day ahead.
Grate sharp
Cheddar
cheese
or
place
American cheese slices on top
of prepared pizza dough.
Grate potatoes over cheese and spread evenly, then grate onion over potatoes. Drizzle with butter;
season with salt and pepper and top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Cook for 5 minutes more or until shrimp is opaque.
Serve over 3/4 cup cooked angel hair pasta.

title: creamy salad dressing
directions: Whisk together salad dressing, yogurt, catsup, lemon juice and pepper in a bowl until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Steam broccoli.
Dice tomatoes.
Blend together mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Toss with vegetables.

title: pierogies
directions: Boil and mash potatoes; add next 4 ingredients.
Let cool. Add warm water to flour and salt.
Knead well by hand until dough is smooth and flexible and does not stick to hands.
Roll 1/8-inch thick and cut out circles.
Place 1 tablespoon of filling on each circle and fold in half.
Seal the edges by pinching with fingers. Drop into boiling water for approximately 3 minutes.
Remove at once; drain off water and place on a cloth.
Cool; freeze.

title: hawaiian cole slaw
directions: Mix pineapple and cabbage together.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and carrot; mix all together.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake rolls as directed, leaving flat in baking pan.
Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing together.
Spread over dough when cooled. Top with vegetables and cheese.
Serve.

title: greek feta chicken
directions: Whisk first four ingredients in medium bowl.
Add chicken and turn to coat.
Cover and let stand at least 30 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Make 24 hours ahead.

title: fig preserve cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, sugar and spices.
Add oil and beat well.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Add buttermilk gradually.
Add figs, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
When cake is done while hot pour sauce over cake in pan.

title: bacon cornmeal biscuits
directions: Sift together the flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl.
Cut in margarine or butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in the center, add milk, onion and bacon.
Stir just until dough clings together.
Knead dough gently on a lightly floured surface, 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll or pat dough to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter, dipping cutter in flour between cuts.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake in a 450° oven for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate cake (eggless)
directions: You may add egg, if you wish.
Use white for boiled frosting. You can substitute 1 square chocolate for cocoa.
Use 1/2 tablespoon, less shortening.
Bake in a 9-inch bread pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until center springs back.

title: granny's cole slaw
directions: Mix together the cabbage, salt, chopped celery, chopped pepper and chopped carrots.
Allow to stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze out all excess liquid.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar, celery and mustard seed; boil for 1 minute and cool.
Pour liquid mixture over cabbage and mix well.
Put in freezer containers and freeze or refrigerate until served.

title: turkey corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add broth and bring to boil.
Add potatoes, celery and carrots. Reduce heat; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and heat through.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple, onion, pepper and 1 cup pecans.
Form into 2 balls; roll each ball in remaining cup of pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Well grease a tube pan.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix 3/4 cup of sugar and the cinnamon in a plastic bag; drop biscuit pieces in (I do one can at a time) and shake to coat each one.
Drop biscuit pieces evenly into the tube cake pan.

title: angel food and jello dessert
directions: Fix jello according to the directions that are on the jello package, using juice from thawed strawberries to make up for the cold water.
Add the strawberries to the jello mixture.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Cream together cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Set aside.
Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Place second mixture on bottom of cupcake liners.
Drop large spoonful of cream cheese filling on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: peanut butter cake by janet
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 35 to 40 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding mix together until well blended. Add other ingredients, chill and serve.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine the last 6 ingredients and spoon over mixture of the first 6 ingredients.

title: wassillubbock, texas
directions: Simmer the above, strain (I don't) then you add a jigger of rum/to a cup (I didn't).

title: white chili
directions: Cook beans, broth, garlic and half the onions in a large soup pot.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Simmer 2 hours.
Saute remaining onions in oil in a skillet until tender.
Add chilies and seasonings and mix thoroughly.
Add mixture to beans and simmer another 1/2 hour.
Serve topped with grated cheese and cornbread on the side.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar.
Add oatmeal and other ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes. Fruit may be added before baking.

title: honey pecan balls
directions: Cream shortening. Add honey, then flour, salt and vanilla. Mix well and add nuts. Form into small balls on greased cookie sheet. Cook at 300° for 30 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while still hot. Cool, then roll again.

title: terry's good stuff
directions: In a large bowl, prepare pudding according to package directions. When pudding starts to thicken, fold in Cool Whip. In a 13 x 9 inch pan, place a layer of graham crackers. Spread a layer of pudding over the graham crackers. Continue alternating layers of graham crackers and pudding ending with pudding layer. Refrigerate overnight. Cover with chocolate syrup before serving.

title: pizza alfredo
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Warm Alfredo sauce to room temperature. Spread over pizza crust.
Place all toppings over the sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spiced cranberries(4 cups)
directions: Wash cranberries; do not dry!
Cook cranberries and sugar over low heat in a saucepan until sugar dissolves.
Add vinegar and cinnamon.
Cook until cranberries pop.
You can put in jar and seal like jam.
A great gift.
Good with turkey or game.

title: monkey coffee cake
directions: Cut biscuits into four pieces each. Shake in bag or covered bowl with sugar and cinnamon.
Lay in a 9 x 9-inch square pan or Bundt pan, greased. Cover with Sauce and nuts, if desired.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on high, stirring all the time.
(It will smoke and peanuts will crackle.)
When syrup spins a thread, stir in 1 tablespoon soda.
Stir fast and pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
Spread thin fast.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 1 minute in blender on high.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients to form a ball.
Refrigerate.
Roll ball in crushed nuts before serving.

title: healthy pita pocket
directions: Fill pita pocket with all other ingredients.

title: chalupa - a chili style stew
directions: Wash pinto beans and roast.
Put all ingredients into a large crock-pot.
Add water to almost the rim.
Cook overnight.
Stir once or twice.
This stew may be served over any kind of nacho chips, with shredded cheese, lettuce, tomato and sour cream (optional).
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk thoroughly.
Add a few drops of red food coloring for deeper color.
Add cherry pie mix and pineapple.
Chill or freeze overnight.

title: noodle clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanuts and noodles.
Use a heaping teaspoonful of prepared mixture and drop on waxed paper to form a cluster.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix thoroughly the Eagle Brand and lemon juice.
Add the well drained, crushed pineapple, chopped nuts, cake color and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: spaghetti and meat
directions: Brown meat in small amount of fat.
Add onion and seasoning and simmer 15 minutes.
Add dry spaghetti to mixture and cook until done (10 to 12 minutes).

title: crackers pie
directions: Mix and pour in greased pie pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot ring with peas(recipe of past president mrs. helen r. cornelison, h. l., sr.)
directions: Cook carrots until tender; press through a ricer and measure 2 cups.
Season.
Beat eggs slightly and add milk, then blend with carrot mixture.
Pour into well-greased ring mold and set in a pan of warm water.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven for 35 minutes.
The center is filled with fresh peas topped with whipped cream.

title: bo's cheese and crackers
directions: Lay cheese on top of crackers. Place dish in microwave.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: creole relish
directions: Combine all ingredients on 18 inch square sheet of heavy duty aluminum foil.
Fold up butcher wrap style.
Place on grid over medium coals for 6 minutes per side.
Serve warm.
Makes 3 cups of relish.

title: hunters gumbo
directions: Place squash, peppers and tomatoes in large kettle.
Cook on low for 1 hour.
Flour meat and brown in bacon drippings along with onion.
Add to kettle.
Simmer another hour.
Add mushrooms and seasonings.
Cook until liquid is reduced to consistency of stew.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice and corn bread.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Simmer zucchini, covered, until tender for about 6 to 8 minutes in a small amount of water.
Shake the pan to keep them from sticking.
Drain well.
Combine sour cream, butter, Parmesan, salt and paprika.
Stir this mixture over a low flame until well mixed. Remove from fire and stir in egg yolk and chopped onion.
Add the zucchini.
Place mixture in a baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese and buttered crumbs.
Bake in 375° oven until brown.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: In heavy
pan
mix together well the flour, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add
milk
and
cook about 2 minutes.
Remove from fire; add
beaten
egg
yolks,
vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top
with	meringue or whipped cream.
Make meringue with 2	egg whites and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in slow oven until golden brown.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain.
Separate dough in triangles and press together on pizza pan, sealing perforations.
Spoon sausage over dough and top with hash browns and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings and pour over sausage.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the cubed potatoes, water, onion, marjoram, bouillon granules and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes or until the potatoes are tender.
Mash potatoes slightly, but do not drain. In a screw-top jar, combine 1/2 cup of the milk and the flour. Cover and shake well.
Stir milk mixture into potato mixture along with the remaining milk and cheese.
Cook and stir until thickened, bubbly and cheese is melted.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Stir in bacon and parsley.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 side-dish servings.

title: strawberry delicious rhubarb pie
directions: Slice strawberries and rhubarb into small 1/8-inch cubes.
Roll out 1 pie crust dough into pie pan.
Arrange raw, washed rhubarb along bottom.
Mix strawberries, sugar and flour together in a medium bowl.
Put mixture on top of rhubarb evenly.
Cut crisscross strips for top of pie crust from the second pie crust dough. Spread strips across top in cross-cross pattern.
Pur about 2 to 3 tablespoons butter or margarine dotted on top of pie.
Bake at 425° for about 40 minutes, until browned.

title: graham crackers eclairs
directions: Line a 9 x 13 pan with graham crackers. Blend pudding and milk. Add Cool Whip. Pour half of mixture over crackers. Repeat one more time with crackers and remaining pudding mix. Place crackers on last mixture. Heat a can of icing in microwave for 30 seconds. Stir and spread over crackers. Refrigerate overnight.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Set aside.
Blend potatoes and butter/margarine until smooth.
Gradually add remaining ingredients until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Keep potato candy in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place boneless and skinless chicken pieces in bottom of baking dish.
Pour soup over chicken.
tags: cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup or cream of broccoli soup

title: chow mein cookies
directions: Melt bits.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients and mix.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Chop veggies; blend all ingredients and cook for 1 to 2 hours. Season with Mrs. Dash or any preferred no-salt seasoning.
Free exchange, except for sugar veggies.
This is a great soup if you are watching your weight.
Enjoy any time of the day.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: On a low heat, melt margarine in pan.
Add marshmallows.
When melted, turn off.
Add cut up cherries, cut up gum candy, raisins, pecans and graham crackers crumbs.
Mix well and place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: grandma jeanette spruill's tomato pudding
directions: Mix tomatoes, sugar and butter in a saucepan on stove until it comes to a good boil, then add your thickening.
Pour all in a glass baking dish and add biscuits or bread crumbs.
Put in stove and bake at 350° until crumbs turn brown. Good eating.

title: after-school snack
directions: Place raisins in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine butter and brown sugar in saucepan.
Cook and stir into hard ball. Spread over raisins.
Top with chocolate bits, spreading as they melt.
Chill until firm.
Cut into pieces.

title: pecan praline cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar until creamy.
Add 6 eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add lemon juice, vanilla and flour.
Fold into stiff batter.
Add pecans.
Stir and press into well-greased Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside and mix egg, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese.
Pour over crust and bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Add lemon juice to pie filling and pour over cooled base.
Chill until served.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: carla's lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Combine tomato sauce, garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper in a large frying pan.
Boil lasagna noodles until done.

title: country corn
directions: Cook Shoepeg corn on medium heat in shortening until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix milk, egg and oil in a small bowl.
Add milk mixture to dry ingredients and stir until moist (batter will be slightly lumpy).
Pour into lined muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 muffins.

title: it's a winner chili
directions: Sear meat in covered 2-quart pan with vegetable oil. Add tomato sauce, onion and garlic powder. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour. Stir occasionally. Add water if necessary. Simmer for 30
more minutes. Serve with a side dish of pinto beans, chopped onions or Cheddar cheese for garnishes. Yield: 10 servings.

title: poached trout
directions: Place fish in skillet; add milk, water, lemon slices, allspice, salt and parsley.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes, until tender.
Remove to hot platter.
Combine white sauce, lemon juice and eggs; pour over fish and serve.

title: after dinner mint ice cream pie
directions: Thaw ice cream at room temperature for 10 to 15 minutes.
Fill pie crusts with ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: good and easy chicken breasts
directions: Place skinless chicken breasts, rib side down, in a baking pan and pour apple butter over them.
I use about 28 ounces of apple butter for 12 breasts.
The amount can vary depending on how many you're cooking.
A little water can be added to stretch the apple butter.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours. You can also cook them on top of the stove using a coated covered skillet and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked apple pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt 2 extra tablespoons of butter in a 9-inch pie plate.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Combine with brown sugar, cinnamon and melted butter.
In another bowl, mix flour, milk, eggs and salt.
Pour into pie plate.
Place apple mixture in center of milk mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes. Delicious!!

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Mix jello in 9 x 12-inch pan, then add cranberry sauce, apple, pineapple, nuts and celery.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Chop vegetables.
Mix with bacon and Mozzarella cheese.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix altogether.
Cook until thick, then add to baked pie shell.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter; beat eggs and add sugar, flour and vanilla.
Add chocolate mixture to egg mixture and put in greased and floured cake or pie tin.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. It will puff and fall.
May be served with scoop of ice cream on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease and flour bread pan.
In large bowl mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda with fork.
"Cut" in shortening (like when making pie).
"With fork" stir in bananas and eggs just until blended; spread in pan.
(Also stir in nuts, if desired.) Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool about 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Do not mix, just layer the ingredients in the same order listed.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Completely cool before cutting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form ball.
Roll ball with remaining 1/2 nuts.

title: carrot soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Place onion in saucepan with carrots, celery, water and Herb-Ox.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into blender and blend 10 seconds.
Add salt, pepper and half and half.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Serve immediately or refrigerate and reheat to serve.
Serves approximately 6.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cake:
Add flour, Jell-O, water, oil and unbeaten eggs to cake mix in a bowl.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed with mixer or beat until smooth.
Add the frozen strawberries and beat 1 minutes or until mixed well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch layer pan.
Bake in a 350° gas oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Strawberry Icing when cooled.

title: country-style vanilla ice cream
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Cream vanilla and salt, mix thoroughly and chill.
Then churn until it freezes.
Yields around 3 quarts.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a glass casserole dish that has been greased (7 x 11-inch).
Combine brown sugar, flour, pecans and butter.
Mix well.
Sprinkle on top of potato mixture in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pig pickin barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Makes 1 quart.

title: crunchy peanut brittle
directions: Line a large electric skillet with heavy-duty foil.
Combine sugar, water and syrup in skillet.
Set temperature gauge at 375°. Cook, stirring occasionally, until syrup turns golden.
Stir in peanuts and salt.
Continue stirring until mixture becomes brown. Unplug skillet, then vigorously stir in margarine and soda.
Remove foil with candy still on foil.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: casseroled barbecued chicken
directions: Dip chicken into flour and salt mix.
Brown in fat.
Put chicken in casserole dish.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of fat in skillet.
Saute onions, celery and green pepper until golden brown.
Blend in other ingredients.
Pour sauce over chicken. Bake, covered, at 350° for 90 minutes.
Good with cinnamon-stick tea, sweetened.

title: fudgy buttons
directions: Add cocoa to melted butter and mix well. Stir in sugar. Add milk and stir until smooth. Add peanut butter and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper; flatten tops and shape into 1-inch patties.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla extract until smooth, then fold in Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust and chill for 4 to 5 hours or overnight until set.

title: general tso's chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, vinegar, 1/2 cup water, garlic and ginger root in a bowl.
Combine egg and cornstarch in another bowl and dip chicken pieces.
Heat oil in a wok or deep, heavy skillet until very hot, add the chicken and fry for 4 to 6 minutes, or until crisp.
Transfer chicken with tongs to paper towels to drain.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of oil from wok.
Add soy sauce mixture, chili peppers and chicken. Cook the mixture over moderately high heat for 5 minutes, or until heated through. Serve with steamed vegetables, fried rice or noodles.
Enjoy!

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine rice, seasoning packet from rice mix and hot water. Place in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside. Sprinkle pork chops with pepper and place over rice mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover casserole, combine cream of celery soup and milk.
Pour over casserole.
Bake casserole, uncovered, 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: creamy carrots
directions: Wash and scrape carrots.
Cut into quarters, lengthwise.
Put carrots in boiling water; add salt and sugar.
Cover.
Cook until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Blend mayonnaise and cream. Pour over carrots and mix lightly.
Serve at once.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Then, take a small amount and add to beaten egg yolks.
Return this to chocolate mixture and cook and stir until very thick.
Remove from heat and add oleo and vanilla. Beat vigorously.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls; cover and refrigerate at least one hour.
Thread meatballs on skewers, leaving space between each.
Grill for 6 minutes per side over medium-hot coals.
Garnish with pineapple chunks, papaya chunks or kiwi fruit slices.
Serves 4 or makes 20 appetizers.
